Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.75,0:00:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时在夜深人静的时候\N{\rEng}Sometimes Dr. Lecter and I would talk...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.03,0:00:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生会和我聊聊天\N{\rEng}when things got quiet enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.12,0:00:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谈我所选修的科学课程\N{\rEng}about the science courses I was takin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.28,0:00:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那种邮购的心理学课程  也能称为科学?\N{\rEng}Some kind of mail-order courses in psychology, Nurse Barney?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.25,0:00:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然不是\N{\rEng}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.74,0:00:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并不认为心理学是科学\N{\rEng}I don't consider psychology a science...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.70,0:00:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生也不这么想\N{\rEng}and neither did Dr. Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么  巴尼...\N{\rEng}Now, Barney...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.61,0:01:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你在收容所工作的时候\N{\rEng}while you were working at the asylum...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.24,0:01:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的确看到史达琳和汉尼拔之间有互动关系\N{\rEng}you observed Clarice Starling and Hannibal Lecter interacting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.37,0:01:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,互动?\N{\rEng}Interacting?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.12,0:01:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是聊天之类的\N{\rEng}Talking to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.95,0:01:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  他们看起来好像是...\N{\rEng}Yes. Yes, it seemed to me that they...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.83,0:01:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你很想拿这笔咨询费\N{\rEng}I can see you're eager to justify your consulting fee...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.45,0:01:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是只说你看到的\N{\rEng}but why don't we start with what you saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.70,0:01:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别把自己的想法加进去\N{\rEng}not what you thought about what you saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.83,0:01:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  别这样  他当然可以表达自己的意见\N{\rEng}Cordell, don't be like that. Barney can give us his opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.37,0:01:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼  告诉我们你的看法\N{\rEng}Barney, give us your opinion of what you saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.66,0:01:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得他们之间是哪种关系?\N{\rEng}What was it between them?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.42,0:01:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通常汉尼拔医生  根本不理会来访的观察员\N{\rEng}Most of the time, Dr. Lecter didn't respond at all to visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.66,0:01:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至会不发一言的瞪着前来观察的学生\N{\rEng}He'd just, for instance, open his eyes long enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.58,0:01:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让他们觉得难堪\N{\rEng}to insult some academic who was there to look over him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.28,0:01:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他却回答史达琳的问话\N{\rEng}With Starling, he answered her questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.99,0:01:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她引起了他的兴趣  也被她深深的吸引住\N{\rEng}She interested him. She intrigued him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.87,0:02:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他认为她既迷人又有趣\N{\rEng}He thought she was charming and amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.29,0:02:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以史达琳和汉尼拔...\N{\rEng}So Clarice Starling and Hannibal Lecter...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.33,0:02:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就变成了朋友\N{\rEng}became friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.33,0:02:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错  是一种形而上的朋友\N{\rEng}Inside a kind of formal structure, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.33,0:02:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么说来他很喜欢她?\N{\rEng}And he was fond of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.92,0:02:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.21,0:02:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼  谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you, Barney.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.58,0:02:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你的坦白\N{\rEng}Thank you very much for your candor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于你卖给我的那些...\N{\rEng}And keep all those wonderful items...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.04,0:02:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔的珍贵收藏品\N{\rEng}from your personal Lecter treasure trove coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.84,0:02:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我非常喜欢\N{\rEng}I've enjoyed them immensely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.70,0:02:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生\N{\rEng}Mr. Verger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.50,0:02:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喔  我差点忘了\N{\rEng}Oh, I almost forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.12,0:02:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  我能吃块甜点吗?\N{\rEng}I might be able to get a cookie down. What do you say, Cordell?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那会要了你的命\N{\rEng}I think it would kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-多少钱?  -二十五...\N{\rEng}- How much? - Two hundred and fifty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.96,0:02:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万\N{\rEng}Thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.50,0:02:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去开张二十五万的支票\N{\rEng}Cut a check for $250,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.26,0:03:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}{\fad(500,500)}{\i1}{\pos(182,248)}{\fs50}{\c&H19125D&}{\fn方正硬笔行书简体}汉 尼 拔
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.67,0:04:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种时候她也能睡\N{\rEng}How can she sleep at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.55,0:05:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她昨晚出勤  现在正养精蓄锐\N{\rEng}She's on a jump-out squad all night. She's saving her strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.17,0:05:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说从华府警局  来了个叫柏顿的家伙\N{\rEng}We got some guy named Bolton from the DC Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家请注意  这是现场区域图\N{\rEng}All right, everyone. Pay attention. Here's the layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  我是华府警探柏顿\N{\rEng}Excuse me. I'm Officer Bolton, DC Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好  从警徽上我可以看出来\N{\rEng}I can see that from your badge. How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是这里的负责人\N{\rEng}I'm in charge here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.88,0:05:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏顿警探  我是史达琳探员\N{\rEng}Officer Bolton, I'm Special Agent Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了避免不必要的误会\N{\rEng}Just so we don't get off on the wrong foot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.43,0:05:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我解释一下我们来此的目的\N{\rEng}let me explain why we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.67,0:05:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对艾微达很了解  因为我曾逮捕过她两次\N{\rEng}I'm here because I know Evelda Drumgo. I arrested her twice on RICO warrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.88,0:05:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次因为牵涉到毒品和枪械\N{\rEng}DEA and ATF, in addition to backing me up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.59,0:06:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,禁药取缔局和武器管理局  也一起参加行动\N{\rEng}are here for the drugs and the weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于你来这里是因为市长在被判了使用可卡因罪后\N{\rEng}You're here because our mayor wants to appear tough on drugs...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.67,0:06:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了表现出取缔毒品的决心\N{\rEng}especially after his own cocaine conviction...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.01,0:06:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才让你们加入我们的行动\N{\rEng}and hopes he can accomplish that by having you join us here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.67,0:06:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小姐  你倒挺凶的嘛\N{\rEng}You got a smart mouth, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不介意  我们可以继续讨论吗?\N{\rEng}If you wouldn't mind, I'd appreciate it if you'd let me continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  大家看一下\N{\rEng}All right, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲜鱼市场的后面是水\N{\rEng}Fish market. Back's on the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对面是毒品制造所\N{\rEng}Across the street, ground floor, is the meth lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}通缉犯
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.26,0:06:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾微达是爱滋病患者\N{\rEng}Evelda Drumgo's HIV positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,紧要关头她会又抓又咬  你们要小心\N{\rEng}She will spit and bite if cornered, so you should watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.21,0:06:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏顿  万一是你在媒体前\N{\rEng}If you happen to be the one who puts her in a patrol car...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.13,0:06:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,送她进警车  千万别碰她的头\N{\rEng}in front of the news cameras, Bolton, you don't wanna push her head down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为她喜欢把针藏在头发里\N{\rEng}She'll likely have a needle in her hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.60,0:06:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好能在室内将她拿下\N{\rEng}We want to take her inside the building, not out in the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}公共市场
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.46,0:06:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家尽量靠近我们的伪装车\N{\rEng}We can get closest with the van.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.55,0:06:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时候我们从前面进攻  禁药组攻打后面\N{\rEng}If it looks good, on my signal we hit the front, DEA hits the back...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请华府警探去支援禁药组\N{\rEng}DCPD backin'them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的瞭望员会守在三条街前\N{\rEng}She'll have her watchers out at least three blocks around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以便及时给她消息  所以我们不要太招摇\N{\rEng}They've tipped her before in time, so let's not make spectacles of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.47,0:07:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-今天挺忙碌的  -没错\N{\rEng}- Pretty busy today. - I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.72,0:07:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请给我杯咖啡\N{\rEng}Can I please get a cup of coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你看到了吗?  -那表示可以行动\N{\rEng}- Did you see that? - That's a roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,近来如何?\N{\rEng}What's up, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.76,0:07:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死  她出来了\N{\rEng}Goddamn it. It's her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.23,0:08:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有三个人  都带着枪\N{\rEng}With three guys. They're all packin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.55,0:08:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她胸前挂着东西  是婴儿\N{\rEng}She's carryin' something. She's got a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏汉  人太多\N{\rEng}Hey, Brigham, it's too crowded.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.06,0:08:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看取消比较好\N{\rEng}There are too many people. I say we call it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.30,0:08:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说呢?\N{\rEng}What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我同意\N{\rEng}I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有单位  行动取消\N{\rEng}All units, stand down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-威士基知道了  -柏克知道了\N{\rEng}- Whiskey team copies. - Burke copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.43,0:08:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是柏顿  我要继续行动\N{\rEng}This is Bolton. Stay on target.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.38,0:08:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏顿  我已说过取消行动\N{\rEng}I said all units stand down, Bolton, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-太晚了  我们已经开始  -柏顿  请你合作\N{\rEng}- It's too late. We're movin'in. - Bolton, he said it's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.39,0:08:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不准行动\N{\rEng}Stand down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为她胸前有婴儿  重复她有婴儿\N{\rEng}She's carrying a baby. I repeat, she's carrying a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.31,0:08:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有单位不要行动\N{\rEng}All units stand down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.84,0:08:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-柏顿  把枪收起来  -要命  有人拿枪\N{\rEng}- Keep that gun down, Bolton. - Damn, dude got a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.97,0:08:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-先杀了他  -快走!\N{\rEng}- Light his ass up. - It's a go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.81,0:08:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,调查局  快趴在地上\N{\rEng}FBI! Down on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,停火\N{\rEng}Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.35,0:09:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要开枪\N{\rEng}Hold your fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.35,0:09:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别开枪\N{\rEng}Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.68,0:09:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾微达  你出来\N{\rEng}Evelda, get out of the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.97,0:09:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是史达琳吗?\N{\rEng}Starling, is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.81,0:09:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你离开车子\N{\rEng}Step away from the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把手举起来\N{\rEng}Show me your hands, Evelda.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.35,0:09:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请把手举起来\N{\rEng}Please. Show me your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你近来好吗?\N{\rEng}How've you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.18,0:09:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别这样做\N{\rEng}Don't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.97,0:09:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做什么?\N{\rEng}Do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.31,0:10:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  不会有事的\N{\rEng}It's all right. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.65,0:10:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道  宝贝  你吓坏了\N{\rEng}I know, I know. Baby, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.68,0:10:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别哭\N{\rEng}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你别哭\N{\rEng}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.60,0:10:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事的\N{\rEng}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今早朋友家人和同事  聚集在阿灵顿国家公墓中\N{\rEng}Friends, family and coworkers gathered here this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参加因公殉职的武器管制局\N{\rEng}at Arlington National Cemetery to bury BATF AgentJohn Brigham...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.98,0:11:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏汉探员的丧礼  他享年四十岁\N{\rEng}shot and killed in the line of duty Friday. He was 40 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.40,0:11:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场毒品突击  夺去他及另外五个人的生命\N{\rEng}This ill-fated drug raid that claimed his life and five others...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一连串的意外事件\N{\rEng}is the latest in a seemingly endless series of incidents...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,始于德州的瓦库\N{\rEng}beginning with Waco, Texas...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.31,0:11:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于探员们只知使用武力  而不愿运用大脑一事\N{\rEng}in which theJustice Department and the FBI have been questioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.73,0:11:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司法部及调查局已受到质询\N{\rEng}about their use of firepower rather than judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.68,0:11:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次的灾难是由调查局探员\N{\rEng}This time it was FBI Special Agent Clarice Starling...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.44,0:11:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳所引起\N{\rEng}heading up the calamitous strike force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.27,0:11:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十年前  为了营救前田纳西议员的女儿凯瑟琳\N{\rEng}Agent Starling attained some measure of celebrity ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.93,0:11:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳曾经由"食人魔"汉尼拔医生的协助\N{\rEng}when she was given information by Dr. Hannibal "The Cannibal"Lecter...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.35,0:11:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得以破案...\N{\rEng}which led to the rescue of Catherine Martin...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.61,0:11:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她因此而声名大噪\N{\rEng}daughter of the former US senator from Tennessee.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.07,0:11:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是这个礼拜当她恢复工作时\N{\rEng}When she returns to work this week,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.46,0:11:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迎接她的不是表扬而是诉讼\N{\rEng}she won't be so celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.94,0:11:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为代表被害家属的泰福律师\N{\rEng}Attorney Telford Higgins, representing one of the families of those slain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.98,0:11:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将控告她误杀至死之罪\N{\rEng}says he will file a wrongful-death suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.14,0:11:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德!\N{\rEng}Cordell!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.85,0:12:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德!\N{\rEng}Cordell!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.77,0:12:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有什么吩咐  -替我接司法部\N{\rEng}- Yes, sir. - Get me theJustice Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.44,0:12:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员?\N{\rEng}Agent Starling?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是禁药取缔局的约翰  助理执政官诺门\N{\rEng}This is John Eldridge from DEA. Assistant Director Noonan, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.14,0:12:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们部门的拉金  他专精责任问题\N{\rEng}Larkin Wayne from our Office of Professional Responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.35,0:12:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,武器管制局的包勃\N{\rEng}Bob Sneed, ATF.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.44,0:12:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,市长助理班尼  还有司法部的保罗\N{\rEng}Benny Holcombe, assistant to the mayor. And Paul Krendler.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.69,0:12:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该认识他\N{\rEng}You know Paul. Paul's come over from Justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.31,0:12:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他以非官方身份来协助我们\N{\rEng}unofficially, as a favor to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说  他并不在这里\N{\rEng}In other words, he's here, and he's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想你已经看过  报纸和电视的报导吧\N{\rEng}So I take it you've seen the coverage in the papers and on television?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.52,0:12:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些新闻和我无关\N{\rEng}I have nothing to do with the news, Mr. Krendler.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.19,0:12:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个女人手中抱着婴儿\N{\rEng}The woman had a baby in her arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.07,0:12:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,照片就在这里  你应该知道问题有多严重\N{\rEng}There are pictures. You could see the problem, I would think.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.14,0:12:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婴儿是在她胸前挂的婴儿袋里\N{\rEng}Not in her arms. In a carrier across her chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.52,0:12:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她手里抱的是冲锋枪\N{\rEng}In her arms she had a MAC-10.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.78,0:12:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是来帮你的\N{\rEng}Look, we're here to help you, Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这样怒气冲冲的态度  只会使事情更难办\N{\rEng}It's gonna be a hell of a lot harder to do with a combative attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.07,0:13:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能自由发言吗?\N{\rEng}Can I speak freely, Mr. Pearsall?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.27,0:13:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是应你们的要求  来协助做这次突击的\N{\rEng}Your agency called this office to get me assigned to help you on this raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的确尽力去做\N{\rEng}I tried to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.49,0:13:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有人却不遵守我所做的判断\N{\rEng}I clearly expressed my judgment and was ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.56,0:13:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以致牺牲了一位好朋友也是好探员\N{\rEng}And now a good agent and a friend is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别忘了你还杀了五个人\N{\rEng}You shot and killed five people out there, Agent Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道能说这是好的判断吗?\N{\rEng}Is that how you define good judgment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.57,0:13:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一场丑恶的突击\N{\rEng}This raid was an ugly mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.78,0:13:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被迫在被杀\N{\rEng}I ended up in a position where I had a choice of dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.99,0:13:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和射杀身挂婴儿的女人中做选择\N{\rEng}or shooting a woman carrying a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.06,0:13:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我做了选择\N{\rEng}I chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是射杀她\N{\rEng}I shot her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.98,0:13:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我杀了带着婴儿的母亲\N{\rEng}I killed a mother holding her child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.57,0:13:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很后悔  也恨我自己\N{\rEng}And I regret it. I resent myself for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.15,0:13:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起  现在要终止这个会议\N{\rEng}Gentlemen, I'm going to call a halt to this meeting...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会个别打电话给你们\N{\rEng}and get back to you individually by phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.52,0:14:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真会浪费时间\N{\rEng}That was a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  你居然有秘密仰慕者\N{\rEng}You have a secret admirer, Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他本身不怎么样  却有身居高位的朋友\N{\rEng}He isn't much to look at, but he does have friends in high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.36,0:14:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你记得马森·维杰吗?\N{\rEng}Remember Mason Verger?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔的第四个被害人\N{\rEng}Lecter's fourth victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.95,0:14:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很富有\N{\rEng}The rich one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.53,0:14:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是唯一死里逃生的人\N{\rEng}The only one that survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说有些汉尼拔的新资料  但是只愿意告诉你\N{\rEng}He says he has some new information on Lecter he'll only share with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.82,0:14:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么意思?  如有需要  就扣押文件呀\N{\rEng}What do you mean, only share it with me? You want it, seize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-最好别这么做  -我并没有和你讲话\N{\rEng}- I'd rather not. - I wasn't speaking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.78,0:14:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我和你讲话时  自然会看着你\N{\rEng}When I speak to you, you'll know it because I'll look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.03,0:14:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不这么做?\N{\rEng}Why would we rather not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.62,0:14:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上次他因为我们把汉尼拔从十大通缉犯中除去而打电话来\N{\rEng}The last time he called was when we took Lecter off the Ten Most Wanted List.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很生气  我们对他说 "嘿  你最好接受"\N{\rEng}He was upset about that. We said, "Hey, that's life."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说 "参议院的失察委员会\N{\rEng}He said, "This is a Senate Oversight Committee...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.39,0:14:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}爱序山庄
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.27,0:14:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会给你们好看的"\N{\rEng}to make your life miserable."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他家族对政治上献金一向慷慨\N{\rEng}His family's political contributions may not be enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.07,0:14:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然买不起参议员\N{\rEng}to buy a senator...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.86,0:14:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是绝对租得起\N{\rEng}but they are enough to rent them from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.70,0:15:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,况且他若真有线索  我们又何必惹他生气\N{\rEng}There's no reason to go through that if he really does have something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.36,0:15:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  其实这件事对你有利\N{\rEng}It's a good deal for you, Starling. You can't pretend it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.66,0:15:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你能再回去侦办知名案件\N{\rEng}Get to go back on a celebrated case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.82,0:15:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,媒体方面  我会替你去和他们交涉\N{\rEng}I'll take care of the media for your Drumgo killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都高兴\N{\rEng}Everyone's gonna be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.74,0:15:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并不高兴\N{\rEng}I'm not happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许你根本就不会高兴\N{\rEng}Well, maybe you're incapable of being happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.74,0:15:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗先生\N{\rEng}Mr. Krendler...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.20,0:15:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道做为一个探员  随时都有死亡的危险\N{\rEng}out on the street, you know you might take a bullet in the line of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.54,0:15:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果怕死  那就不要做\N{\rEng}You accept it or you get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.03,0:15:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们接受这个事实\N{\rEng}You live with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但所不能接受的是\N{\rEng}What you don't expect or accept...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你按照所受过的训练和上级的指示去做\N{\rEng}is taking one in the back in your boss's office...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.49,0:15:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而结果却背上黑锅\N{\rEng}for doing your job exactly as they've taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.74,0:15:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这才叫人气愤\N{\rEng}That makes you unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.49,0:15:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  你说得不错\N{\rEng}Of course you're right, Starling...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.95,0:15:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但毕竟改变不了什么\N{\rEng}but it doesn't change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.04,0:15:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它改变了一切  连我在内\N{\rEng}It changes everything. It changes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.87,0:16:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨  我叫柯德  是维杰先生的私人医生\N{\rEng}Hi, I'm Cordell Doemling, Mr. Verger's private physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\rEng}How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.79,0:16:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,麻烦你把车停到那边\N{\rEng}If you'd be so kind as to park down at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.54,0:16:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,眼睛会随着光线而调整\N{\rEng}One's eyes adjust to the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.78,0:17:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生  史达琳探员来了\N{\rEng}Mr. Verger, Agent Starling is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.12,0:17:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你早  维杰先生\N{\rEng}Good morning, Mr. Verger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.99,0:17:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你开的是福特野马吗?\N{\rEng}Was that a Mustang I heard out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.41,0:17:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.62,0:17:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5000c.c.的引擎?\N{\rEng}Five-liter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.54,0:17:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.29,0:17:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那好快呀\N{\rEng}Fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  你可以离开了\N{\rEng}Cordell, I think you can leave us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.41,0:17:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我留下来可能会有用\N{\rEng}I thought I might stay. Perhaps I could be useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.87,0:17:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去看我的午餐准备得如何\N{\rEng}You could be useful seeing about my lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不介意我把麦克风  夹在你的衣服或枕头上吧\N{\rEng}I'll attach this microphone to your clothing or pillow, if that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.24,0:17:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会的\N{\rEng}By all means.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.50,0:17:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样会比较容易些\N{\rEng}Here, this should make it easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.25,0:18:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对发生在我身上的事\N{\rEng}You know, I thank God...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.82,0:18:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须感谢上帝\N{\rEng}for what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.74,0:18:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这是赎罪\N{\rEng}It was my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.25,0:18:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员  你信主吗?\N{\rEng}Have you accepted Jesus, Agent Starling?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你有信仰吗?  -我家人信奉路德教派\N{\rEng}- Do you have faith? - I was raised Lutheran.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.24,0:18:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是我问的问题\N{\rEng}That's not what I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.91,0:18:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是5143690号史达琳探员\N{\rEng}This is Special Agent Clarice Starling, 5143690...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我作证在三月二十日  维杰已经发誓会说实话\N{\rEng}deposing Mason R. Verger on March 20, sworn and attested.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.28,0:18:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想说我童年时代  在夏令营里的快乐时光\N{\rEng}I want to tell you about summer camp. It was a wonderful childhood experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.33,0:18:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-等会儿再谈吧  -我现在就要说\N{\rEng}- We can get to that later. - We can get to it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这些全有关联\N{\rEng}You see, it all comes to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.38,0:18:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是在我父亲所创办的基督夏令营里\N{\rEng}It was a Christian camp my father founded...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.00,0:18:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它专门收容孤苦无依的孩子们\N{\rEng}for poor, unfortunate, cast-off little boys and girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了一块糖  他们愿做任何事\N{\rEng}who would do anything for a candy bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.41,0:18:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生  我对你的恋童癖不感兴趣\N{\rEng}Mr. Verger, I don't need to know about the sex offenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.04,0:18:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没关系  在美国律师之前我已免疫\N{\rEng}It's all right. I have immunity from the US Attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.58,0:18:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至在上帝面前...\N{\rEng}And I have immunity...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.83,0:19:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也免疫了\N{\rEng}from the risen Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为没人禁得起巧克力糖的诱惑\N{\rEng}And nobody beats the Riz.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在法院指派汉尼拔医生给你前  你是否已经认识他?\N{\rEng}Had you ever seen Dr. Lecter before the court assigned you to him for therapy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.46,0:19:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你指的是...\N{\rEng}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.91,0:19:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,社交上的认识?\N{\rEng}Socially?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  你介意谈论它吗?\N{\rEng}It is what I mean, yes, if you don't mind talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.58,0:19:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会  我并不引以为耻\N{\rEng}No, not at all. I'm not ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.67,0:19:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我没这么说  -我们认识得很平常\N{\rEng}- I didn't say you should be. - No, we met conventionally...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.00,0:19:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是医师和病人的关系\N{\rEng}as doctor and patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.12,0:19:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他怎么会到你住处去?\N{\rEng}How did he end up at your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.00,0:19:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然是我邀他的咯\N{\rEng}I invited him, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.04,0:19:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我邀他到我的临时住所去\N{\rEng}to my pied-a-terre.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.83,0:19:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我穿着最诱人的衣服去开门\N{\rEng}I came to the door in my nicest come-hither outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.09,0:19:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我担心...\N{\rEng}I was concerned...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.16,0:19:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可能会怕我\N{\rEng}that he'd be afraid of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他似乎一点也不在乎\N{\rEng}But he didn't seem to be afraid of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.09,0:19:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在想起来是很可疑\N{\rEng}That's almost funny now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把我的性玩具拿给他看\N{\rEng}I showed him my toys...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.71,0:19:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中包括那套活结装置\N{\rEng}my noose setup, among other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:20:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是可以把自己吊起来  却又不会窒息的装置\N{\rEng}It's where you sort of hang yourself, but not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.04,0:20:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那种感觉真好  如果...\N{\rEng}It feels good while you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.04,0:20:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正你能想像得出来\N{\rEng}well, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.17,0:20:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总归...\N{\rEng}Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.54,0:20:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他说 "维杰..."  -维杰  要不要来点兴奋剂?\N{\rEng}- he said, "Mason..." - Mason, would you like a popper?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.04,0:20:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说 "哇!  当然要"\N{\rEng}And I said, "Would I? Oh, wow!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等药效出来后  我高到极点\N{\rEng}Once that kicked in, I was flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.42,0:20:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说 "让我看看你那种"\N{\rEng}He said, "Mason, show me how you smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.38,0:20:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"能赢得小孩信任的笑容"\N{\rEng}to gain the confidence of a child."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我笑起来时...\N{\rEng}When I smiled...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.08,0:20:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他又说 "我看出来  他们为什么会信任你"\N{\rEng}he said, "Oh, I see how you do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,医生手里拿着镜子的碎片朝我走来\N{\rEng}The good doctor approached me with a piece of broken mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.88,0:20:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"试试用这个"\N{\rEng}"Try this."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.16,0:20:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你脸上的肉割下来\N{\rEng}Try peeling off your face...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.79,0:20:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后拿去喂狗吃\N{\rEng}And feeding it to the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.79,0:20:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行  我还是看得到你的笑容\N{\rEng}No, I can still see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.63,0:20:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再来一次\N{\rEng}Try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是不行\N{\rEng}No, I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.58,0:21:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是所谓的娱乐\N{\rEng}That's entertainment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.46,0:21:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说实话  当时似乎觉得很好玩\N{\rEng}Well, it seemed like a good idea at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你提到最近又有新的线索\N{\rEng}You indicated to me that you'd received some kind of new information.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.76,0:21:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德\N{\rEng}Cordell
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.46,0:21:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是怎么来的?\N{\rEng}Where did this come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.88,0:21:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寄来的  两个星期前到的\N{\rEng}Buenos Aires. I received it two weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.84,0:21:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,外面的信封呢?\N{\rEng}Where's the package it came in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.50,0:21:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问得好  上面并没有写什么重要的东西\N{\rEng}Good question. There was nothing written on it of interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是不是扔了?\N{\rEng}Did we throw it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.08,0:21:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  实在很抱歉\N{\rEng}Yes, I'm afraid we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.17,0:21:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看这个会有帮助吗?\N{\rEng}Oh, dear. You think it'll help?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.01,0:21:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但愿如此\N{\rEng}I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.09,0:21:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望能帮你捉到他\N{\rEng}I hope it'll help you catch him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:22:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以雪你这次不名誉的耻辱\N{\rEng}to help cleanse the stigma of your recent dishonor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你  我走了\N{\rEng}Thank you. That's all I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.84,0:22:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你在收容所和汉尼拔医生谈话时\N{\rEng}Did you find some rapport with Dr. Lecter...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.88,0:22:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有对他产生信赖感?\N{\rEng}in your talks at the asylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.76,0:22:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我在割自己脸时  曾经有过那种感觉\N{\rEng}I know I did while I was peeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.67,0:22:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是用文明的方法交换心得\N{\rEng}We exchanged information in a civil way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.67,0:22:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但还是隔着一层玻璃\N{\rEng}But always through the glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.25,0:22:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.05,0:22:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你很奇怪  -为什么?\N{\rEng}- Isn't it funny? - What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.14,0:22:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对我的脸无动于衷\N{\rEng}You can look at my face...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.46,0:22:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是一听我提上帝  反儿使你胆怯\N{\rEng}but you shied when I said the name of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.09,0:23:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-找到你要找的吗?  -你确定只有这些\N{\rEng}- Finding what you want? - Are you sure this is all of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.47,0:23:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到目前为止  只剩这些\N{\rEng}That's all there is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本来不止的  可惜被人一点一点的拿走了\N{\rEng}There was more, but it's been picked over little by little over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.51,0:23:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些东西在特定市场中  能值不少钱\N{\rEng}You know, this stuff s worth a lot of money in certain circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.76,0:23:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像这里的可卡因一样\N{\rEng}It's kind of like the cocaine that disappears around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.14,0:23:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一点一点的消失掉\N{\rEng}little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.09,0:23:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}巴尔的摩州立法医医院
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.01,0:24:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿  巴尼\N{\rEng}Hey, Barney.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.89,0:24:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还记得我吗?\N{\rEng}Remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.34,0:25:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员  请你声明\N{\rEng}Would you agree for the record, Agent Starling...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.72,0:25:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你并没有把权益念给我听\N{\rEng}that I've not been read my rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.77,0:25:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我声明巴尼并不知道他的权益\N{\rEng}I have not Mirandized Barney. He is unaware of his rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.26,0:25:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你把汉尼拔医生交给田纳西警局后\N{\rEng}So when you turned Dr. Lecter over to the Tennessee police...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.72,0:25:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们对他无礼  如今都死了\N{\rEng}They weren't civil to him. They're all dead now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.89,0:25:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实际上他们只活了三天\N{\rEng}They only survived his company three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.30,0:25:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你却活了六年\N{\rEng}You survived him six years at the asylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.22,0:25:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是怎么做到的?  我觉得这和礼貌无关\N{\rEng}How'd you do that? It wasn't just being civil.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.47,0:25:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有很大的关系\N{\rEng}Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.30,0:25:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他逃走后  你有没有想过他可能来找你?\N{\rEng}Did you ever think, after he escaped, he might come after you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.64,0:25:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.77,0:25:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他曾对我说过在可能的情况下\N{\rEng}He once told me that, whenever feasible...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他宁愿吃无礼之人\N{\rEng}he preferred to eat the rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.30,0:25:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫他们"无礼鼠类"  你呢?\N{\rEng}"Free-range rude," he called 'em. What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.52,0:25:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有没有想过他  或想过他可能会来找你?\N{\rEng}You ever think he might come after you? You ever think about him at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.94,0:25:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天都会想上三十秒\N{\rEng}At least 30 seconds of every day. I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.39,0:25:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像坏习惯一样  戒也戒不掉\N{\rEng}He's always with me, like a bad habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.60,0:25:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的东西  像书  纸  图画等等都到哪里去了\N{\rEng}Do you know what happened to his stuff... his books, papers, drawings?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.60,0:26:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,收容所关闭时  所有的东西都丢了\N{\rEng}Everything got thrown away when the place closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.39,0:26:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,节省经费嘛\N{\rEng}Cutbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.68,0:26:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现由汉尼拔医生签名的那本烹饪之乐杂志\N{\rEng}I just found out that Dr. Lecter's signed copy of TheJoy of Cooking...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.98,0:26:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最近被私人收藏家  以一万六千美金买进\N{\rEng}sold to a private collector for $16,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.64,0:26:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕是仿造品\N{\rEng}It was probably a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.89,0:26:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卖主切结书上的签名是"凯伦·费"\N{\rEng}The seller's affidavit of ownership was signed "Karen Phlox."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.97,0:26:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该认识她\N{\rEng}Do you know Karen Phlox? You should.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.31,0:26:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她曾替你填过工作申请表  最后签上"巴尼"\N{\rEng}She filled out your employment application, but signed it "Barney."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.19,0:26:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有退税单也一样\N{\rEng}Same thing on your tax returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.35,0:26:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你要书  我会试着把它要回来\N{\rEng}You want the book? Maybe I can get it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.35,0:26:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当他攻击护士时  你曾打断他的手臂  我要那张X光片\N{\rEng}I want the x-ray of Lecter's arm you broke in the attack on that nurse...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.85,0:26:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有其它被你拿走的东西\N{\rEng}and everything else you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.94,0:26:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在夜深人静  尖叫声平息之后\N{\rEng}We used to talk about a lot of things at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.72,0:26:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们时常聊天\N{\rEng}after the screamin' finally died down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.27,0:27:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时也谈到你  你想知道他都说些什么吗?\N{\rEng}We talked about you sometimes. You wanna know what he said?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.81,0:27:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把X光片给我\N{\rEng}Go get the x-ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.14,0:27:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是个坏人\N{\rEng}I'm not a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.23,0:27:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没说你是坏人\N{\rEng}I didn't say you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.89,0:27:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奇顿医生才是坏人\N{\rEng}Dr. Chilton was a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.48,0:27:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你第一次访问汉尼拔医生后  他就开始录你们的谈话\N{\rEng}After your first visit, he started taping your conversations with Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.10,0:27:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们非常有价值\N{\rEng}These are valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.10,0:27:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你走吧\N{\rEng}Go on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.23,0:27:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已经哀吊得够久了\N{\rEng}You've grieved long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.85,0:27:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是怎么说的?\N{\rEng}And what'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.06,0:27:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在晚上他怎么说我的?\N{\rEng}What'd he say about me late at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.40,0:27:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他谈到遗传和内心深处的行为\N{\rEng}He was talking about inherited, hardwired behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.35,0:27:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他用鹞鸽的遗传来做比方\N{\rEng}He was using genetics in the roller pigeons as an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.39,0:27:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们喜欢高高的飞到天上  然后炫耀的翻着筋斗俯冲下来\N{\rEng}They fly up in the air, roll backwards in a display, fallin' to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.19,0:27:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鹞鸽分为肤浅和深沉两种\N{\rEng}There are shallow rollers, and there are deep rollers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.68,0:28:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是当两只深沉鹞鸽结合后\N{\rEng}You can't breed two deep rollers...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.77,0:28:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的后代往往会\N{\rEng}or their young, their offspring, will roll all the way down...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.06,0:28:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俯冲撞地而死\N{\rEng}hit and die.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.44,0:28:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼  史达琳探员是只深沉的鹞鸽\N{\rEng}Agent Starling is a deep roller, Barney.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.56,0:28:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只希望她父母中有一个是只肤浅的鹞鸽\N{\rEng}Let us hope one of her parents was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.23,0:28:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你并没有离开正轨\N{\rEng}Surely the odd confluence of events hasn't escaped you, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.27,0:28:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为杰克在我面前向你挑战\N{\rEng}Jack Crawford dangles you in front of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.23,0:28:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我才给你一些帮助\N{\rEng}then I give you a bit of help.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.02,0:28:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你以为是因为...\N{\rEng}Do you think it's because I like to look at you...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.40,0:28:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢边看你  边想着你会有多可口吗?\N{\rEng}and imagine how good you would taste...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.40,0:28:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是这样吗?\N{\rEng}Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.81,0:28:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道  难道是真的?\N{\rEng}I don't know. Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.56,0:28:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我待在这个房间里已经八年\N{\rEng}I've been in this room for eight years now, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.90,0:28:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道在我有生之年  他们是不会让我出去的\N{\rEng}I know they will never, ever let me out while I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.28,0:28:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想能看外面的风景\N{\rEng}What I want is a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.48,0:28:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给我一扇窗户  让我能看到树甚至河流\N{\rEng}I want a window where I can see a tree or even water.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.44,0:28:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想转到联邦收容所去  那样才能远离奇顿医生\N{\rEng}I want to be in a federal institution far away from Dr. Chilton.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.89,0:29:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡波尼图书馆中的书信  可以追溯到十三世纪\N{\rEng}The Capponi correspondence goes back to the 13th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.44,0:29:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于在费尔博士手中\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell might hold in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.32,0:29:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他那非意大利人的手中\N{\rEng}his non-Italian hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.44,0:29:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很可能握有但丁的真迹\N{\rEng}a note from Dante Alighieri himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.94,0:29:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他能分辨出真伪吗?  我不认为\N{\rEng}But would he recognize it? I think not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.98,0:29:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位  你们已经肯定  他对意大利中叶的辨认能力\N{\rEng}Gentlemen, you have examined him in medieval Italian...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.44,0:29:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也承认对一个外国人来说\N{\rEng}and I will not deny that his language is admirable...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.15,0:29:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的文字实在美妙\N{\rEng}for a straniero.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.44,0:29:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他是否真正具有\N{\rEng}But is he acquainted with the personalities...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.78,0:29:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,文艺复兴前佛罗伦斯的气质\N{\rEng}of the pre-Renaissance Firenze?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.44,0:29:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我却有所怀疑\N{\rEng}I think not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.52,0:29:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说不定哪天在卡波尼图书馆中\N{\rEng}What if he came upon a note in the Capponi library...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.28,0:29:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会声称找到了诗人卡瓦澄第的真迹\N{\rEng}say from Guido di Cavalcanti?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.94,0:29:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道他真能分辨出真伪吗?  我不相信\N{\rEng}Would he recognize that? I think not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.81,0:29:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们还在争论吗?\N{\rEng}They're still arguing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.07,0:29:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苏立想让他侄子做这份工作\N{\rEng}Sogliato wants the job for his nephew.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.82,0:30:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是学者们似乎对他们所指定的人很满意\N{\rEng}But the scholars seem satisfied with the temporary guy they appointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.44,0:30:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,倘若他真那么精通但丁\N{\rEng}If he's such an expert on Dante...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.11,0:30:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何不让他发表一场对但丁研究的演讲\N{\rEng}let him lecture on Dante to the Studiolo.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.99,0:30:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好面对但丁的爱好者  -好主意\N{\rEng}- Let him face them if he can. - I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.98,0:30:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就订在十四号好了\N{\rEng}Very well. On the 14th.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.61,0:30:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士吗?\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.36,0:30:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫帕齐  是警察总部的督察\N{\rEng}Chief Inspector Rinaldo Pazzi of the questura.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.27,0:30:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,督察  我能帮什么忙?\N{\rEng}Commendatore, how can I be of service?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.82,0:30:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  我在调查...\N{\rEng}Sorry. I'm investigating the disappearance...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.74,0:30:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前任馆长  辛诺的失踪案件\N{\rEng}of your predecessor, Signor di Bonaventura.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.06,0:30:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不知道是否...  -你这么说  好像我已做了馆长\N{\rEng}- I was wondering if... - "Predecessor" implies I have the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.98,0:30:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是希望如此  可惜他们还没决定\N{\rEng}Unfortunately, I don't. Not yet, though I am hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.78,0:30:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只是支薪给我  让我照顾图书馆而已\N{\rEng}They are letting me look after the library for a stipend.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.36,0:31:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以前的调查员\N{\rEng}The officers who first checked...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.57,0:31:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有找到遗书或自杀信\N{\rEng}didn't find any sort of farewell or suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.74,0:31:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你能...\N{\rEng}I was wondering if you...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.36,0:31:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我在抽屉或书中  找到任何有用的东西\N{\rEng}If I come across anything in the Capponi library stuffed in a drawer or book...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.07,0:31:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定会立刻通知你\N{\rEng}I'll call you at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.12,0:31:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.98,0:31:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被改派任务了\N{\rEng}You've been reassigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.95,0:31:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说什么?\N{\rEng}Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.20,0:31:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记得  你本来在调查莫斯楚的案件\N{\rEng}You were on the II Mostro case, I'm sure I read.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.69,0:31:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没错  -现在却查这个案子\N{\rEng}- Yes, that's right. - Now you're on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.11,0:31:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就我所知  这不是什么大案子\N{\rEng}This is much less grand a case, I would think.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.16,0:31:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果以知名度而言...\N{\rEng}Well, if I thought of my work in those terms...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.90,0:31:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说的不错\N{\rEng}yes, I guess I'd agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.28,0:31:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-调查失踪人口  -你说什么?\N{\rEng}- A missing person. - Sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.78,0:31:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为不平等待遇  还是因为你的能力不够?\N{\rEng}Were you unfairly dismissed from the grander case, or did you deserve it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.82,0:31:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士  让我们再回到原题\N{\rEng}Regarding this one, Dr. Fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.62,0:31:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,辛诺的私人物品  是否仍在图书馆内?\N{\rEng}are the signore's personal effects still at the Palazzo?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.20,0:32:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一共装了四大箱  还有清单\N{\rEng}Packed neatly in four cases with an inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.82,0:32:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是没有遗书\N{\rEng}Alas, no note.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.03,0:32:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会叫人来取  谢谢你的帮忙\N{\rEng}I'll send someone over to pick them up. Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.24,0:32:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿  谢谢你\N{\rEng}Hey, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.61,0:32:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进行的如何?  有线索吗?\N{\rEng}How's it going? Any leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.78,0:32:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是线索  可惜就是找不到他\N{\rEng}Yeah, they're all leads. They just don't lead to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.61,0:32:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真佩服你能天天和这些为伍\N{\rEng}I don't know how you live with this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.70,0:32:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天呀\N{\rEng}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.24,0:32:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这封是世界记录给我的恭贺函\N{\rEng}This is from the Guinness Book of World Records congratulating me...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.95,0:32:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说我创下女调查员中杀人最多的记录\N{\rEng}on being the female FBI agent who has shot and killed the most people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.12,0:33:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能不能请你离开一下\N{\rEng}Would you excuse me, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.12,0:33:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题\N{\rEng}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.70,0:33:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亲爱的史达琳\N{\rEng}Dear Clarice...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.67,0:33:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认真追踪你这次的受辱事件\N{\rEng}I've followed with enthusiasm the course of your disgrace and public shaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.78,0:33:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对自己的受辱并不在乎\N{\rEng}My own never bothered me except for the inconvenience...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.16,0:33:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只对失去自由有所不满\N{\rEng}of being incarcerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.08,0:33:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你的眼界  却让我操心\N{\rEng}But you may lack perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.74,0:34:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从我们在地牢中的讨论中\N{\rEng}In our discussions down in the dungeon...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.95,0:34:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现  你那位做守夜员的父亲\N{\rEng}it was apparent to me that your father, the dead night watchman...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.87,0:34:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你心目中占有很重的份量\N{\rEng}figures largely in your value system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.95,0:34:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当初你最得意  能将杰姆绳之以法\N{\rEng}I think your success in putting an end toJame Gumb's career as a couturier...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.33,0:34:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你觉得  那会使你父亲引以为傲\N{\rEng}pleased you most because you could imagine your father being pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.03,0:34:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜如今你却成了调查局中的老鼠屎\N{\rEng}But now, alas, you're in bad odor with the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.94,0:34:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}调查局探员枪杀五人
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.91,0:34:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你父亲会不会因此而感到丢脸\N{\rEng}Do you imagine your daddy being shamed by your disgrace?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.71,0:34:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是否会躺在棺材中\N{\rEng}Do you see him in his plain pine box...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.74,0:34:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,眼见你手刃这份前途无量的工作\N{\rEng}crushed by your failure...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.83,0:34:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而痛心疾首吗?\N{\rEng}the sorry, petty end of a promising career?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.25,0:34:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这份耻辱最大的影响是什么?\N{\rEng}What is worst about this humiliation, Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.87,0:34:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为你的失败  会影响到你父母的形象?\N{\rEng}Is it how your failure will reflect on your mommy and daddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.08,0:34:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是你害怕从此以后...\N{\rEng}Is your worst fear that people will now and forever believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.92,0:34:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们认为他们只是  住在活动房屋中...\N{\rEng}they were indeed just good old trailer-camp...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.04,0:34:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没用的穷白鬼\N{\rEng}tornado-bait white trash...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.33,0:34:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而你也和他们一样?\N{\rEng}and that perhaps you are too?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.82,0:35:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便一提  我发现在调查局的网页上\N{\rEng}By the way, I couldn't help noticing on the FBI's rather dull web site...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.04,0:35:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我居然从普通罪犯\N{\rEng}that I've been hoisted from the Bureau's archives of the common criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.00,0:35:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,升级到十大通缉犯\N{\rEng}and elevated to the more prestigious Ten Most Wanted List.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.58,0:35:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是巧合  还是你又开始侦办我的案件?\N{\rEng}Is this coincidence, or are you back on the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.87,0:35:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,果真如此  那好  我将从退隐的地方走出\N{\rEng}If so, goody goody, because I need to come out of retirement...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.41,0:35:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再回到公众的生活中去\N{\rEng}and return to public life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.12,0:35:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以想像出  你正坐在黯淡的地下室里\N{\rEng}I imagine you sitting in a dark basement room...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.79,0:35:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埋首于纸堆和电脑荧光幕中\N{\rEng}bent over papers and computer screens.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.91,0:35:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说对了吧\N{\rEng}Is that accurate?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.04,0:35:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员  请告诉我实话\N{\rEng}Please tell me truly, Special Agent Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.42,0:35:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请珍重  你的老友  汉尼拔医生\N{\rEng}Regards, your old pal, Hannibal Lecter, MD.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.96,0:35:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,附注: 我看得出  这不是你的本意\N{\rEng}PS: Clearly this new assignment is not your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.29,0:35:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能是某种交换\N{\rEng}Rather, I suppose, it is part of the bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.37,0:35:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是你仍然接受了\N{\rEng}But you accepted it, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.25,0:35:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的职责是毁灭我\N{\rEng}Yourjob is to craft my doom...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.96,0:35:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以实在不知道  在信尾该怎么祝你\N{\rEng}so I'm not sure how well I should wish you...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.83,0:36:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过我相信  我们将会有很多乐趣\N{\rEng}but I'm sure we'll have a lot of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.37,0:36:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回见\N{\rEng}Ta-ta.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.17,0:36:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"汉"\N{\rEng}"H."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.41,0:36:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在信上...\N{\rEng}On the letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.75,0:36:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到一个局部的指纹\N{\rEng}there's one partial fingerprint here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.67,0:36:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-可是在法庭上还嫌不够  -这一定是他\N{\rEng}- Not enough to hold up in court. - I know it's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.83,0:36:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想知道他在哪里写这封信\N{\rEng}Where he was when he wrote it is what I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.16,0:36:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜从信纸上看不出来\N{\rEng}Well, the paper isn't gonna help.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.58,0:36:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中有亚麻纤维的成份  应该属于奢侈品\N{\rEng}Yes, it's linen fibre, yes, it's on the expensive side...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.59,0:36:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是却不罕见  全球至少有上千家店会卖这种信纸\N{\rEng}but it's not so rare that you won't find it in a thousand stationery stores...throughout the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.17,0:36:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于墨水和腊也是一样\N{\rEng}It's the same with the ink, and the same with the wax.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.96,0:36:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有拉斯维加斯的邮戳\N{\rEng}And your Las Vegas postmark?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.37,0:36:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你打赌  是由重寄邮件服务公司寄的\N{\rEng}You can check it out, but I'll bet you it came from a remailing service.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.25,0:36:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来赌城是他最后的停留点\N{\rEng}Las Vegas would be the last place he'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.67,0:36:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的品味不该这么低\N{\rEng}It'd be an assault on his sense of taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.29,0:36:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你不觉得  有目光在你身上游动吗?\N{\rEng}Don't you feel eyes moving over your body, Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.29,0:37:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当然会感觉得到\N{\rEng}I hardly see how you couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.92,0:37:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人的眼光  会在喜欢的东西上游走\N{\rEng}And don't your eyes move over the things you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.50,0:37:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我是怎么回事\N{\rEng}All right, then. Tell me how.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.55,0:37:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.91,0:37:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在轮到你告诉我了\N{\rEng}It's your turn to tell me, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.17,0:37:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你想再骗我到那个布满动物传染病的岛上去?\N{\rEng}You don't have any more vacations to sell on Anthrax Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.59,0:37:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别忘了我们这是公平交易\N{\rEng}Quid pro quo, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.79,0:37:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉你一件事  你也得告诉我一件事\N{\rEng}I tell you things, you tell me things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.71,0:37:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不谈案子  就说你自己吧\N{\rEng}Not about this case. About yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.17,0:37:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是公平交易\N{\rEng}Quid pro quo.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.88,0:37:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  你愿意吗?\N{\rEng}Yes or no, Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.13,0:37:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,手霜\N{\rEng}Hand cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.92,0:37:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中有龙涎香\N{\rEng}Raw ambergris base.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.75,0:37:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,田纳西的熏衣草\N{\rEng}Tennessee lavender.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.13,0:37:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有一些别的东西\N{\rEng}Trace of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.17,0:37:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,羊毛\N{\rEng}Fleece.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.38,0:37:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错\N{\rEng}Lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.33,0:38:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-龙涎香是什么东西?  -它来自鲸鱼\N{\rEng}- What's ambergris? - Ambergris is a whale product.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.30,0:38:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然我们也喜欢但不准进口\N{\rEng}Alas, much as we'd like to, we can't import it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.22,0:38:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这会危害到稀有动物\N{\rEng}Endangered Species Act.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.08,0:38:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-在哪些国家是合法呢?  -毫无疑问的是日本\N{\rEng}- Where isn't it illegal? - Japan, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.50,0:38:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另外还有一些欧洲国家\N{\rEng}Couple of places in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.71,0:38:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我肯定在巴黎  罗马  阿姆斯特丹可以找到\N{\rEng}You'd almost certainly find it somewhere in Paris...Rome, Amsterdam.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.33,0:38:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伦敦也有可能\N{\rEng}Maybe London.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.67,0:38:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种香味  是照客人的指示以手工合成的\N{\rEng}This bouquet was hand-engineered to someone's specifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.17,0:38:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能知道是出自哪个商店吗?\N{\rEng}Is there a way of knowing which shops?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.89,0:38:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以  我们会给你一张名单\N{\rEng}Of course. We'll give you a list.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.00,0:38:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放心  不会太长\N{\rEng}It'll be short.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.30,0:38:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要歌剧票\N{\rEng}I need opera tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.63,0:38:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我身上没有了\N{\rEng}I don't think I got any on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.17,0:38:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说是卖光了\N{\rEng}It's sold out, whatever it's called.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.80,0:38:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是他那个年轻漂亮的太太  吵着要去看歌剧\N{\rEng}It's the pretty, young wife with the ever-open beak who needs opera tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.30,0:39:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-班尼第  -什么事?\N{\rEng}- Benetti. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.80,0:39:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,倒带\N{\rEng}Rewind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.14,0:39:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行  我正在拷贝\N{\rEng}I can't rewind it. I'm making a copy. I'm recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.67,0:39:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么带子?\N{\rEng}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.09,0:39:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是位在斯卡拉大道上  香水店的防盗录影带\N{\rEng}Security camera from a perfume shop in Via Della Scala.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.97,0:39:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国调查局经由国际刑警组  向我们要求的\N{\rEng}FBI, through Interpol, requested a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.05,0:39:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-为什么?  -他们没说\N{\rEng}- Why? - They didn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.42,0:39:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没说?  -他们的态度很奇怪\N{\rEng}- They didn't say? - No. It was actually kind of weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.64,0:39:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摆明了不告诉我们\N{\rEng}They were making a point not to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.01,0:40:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}调查局探员史达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.22,0:41:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}联邦调查局
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.22,0:41:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}调查局十大在逃通缉犯
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.31,0:41:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}暴戾罪犯的逮捕计划
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.13,0:41:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}警告: 你正企图进入联邦情报局的资料库
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.68,0:41:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们仍要去听歌剧吗?  -是的\N{\rEng}- Are we going to the opera? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.81,0:41:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起  当然要去\N{\rEng}Sorry. Yes, we are going.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.51,0:41:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,买到票了吗?\N{\rEng}You got tickets?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.51,0:41:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还没有  我正要上网查看  一定会买到\N{\rEng}No, but I will. In fact, I was just about to look here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.35,0:41:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托别买得太后面  否则又看不到\N{\rEng}Please, not the back row. I would like to see it this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.72,0:41:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝对不会\N{\rEng}Nowhere near the back row...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.93,0:41:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次不管多贵也要买前座\N{\rEng}no matter what the cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.30,0:41:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}登入
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.89,0:42:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}调查局十大在逃通缉犯
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.39,0:42:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}携带武器并且极度危险
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.06,0:42:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}汉尼拔悬赏金
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.26,0:42:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}搜寻
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.35,0:43:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}找到一个汉尼拔悬赏金
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.43,0:43:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}逮捕汉尼拔归案的悬赏金
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.72,0:43:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}汉尼拔曾是一位出色的精神科医生
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.81,0:43:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}在1990年逃逸之后  成为搜索的焦点
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.31,0:43:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}三百万的赏金将付给能提供线索使他归案的人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.60,0:43:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}想提供汉尼拔线索的人  请打1-212-555-0118
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.23,0:43:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  你有没有想过\N{\rEng}Tell me, Clarice, would you want to harm...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.65,0:43:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去伤害那些迫害过你的人?\N{\rEng}those who forced you to consider it, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.85,0:44:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你尽管承认\N{\rEng}It's perfectly okay to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.06,0:44:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为想向敌人挑战\N{\rEng}It's perfectly au naturel...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.06,0:44:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是人性自然的表现\N{\rEng}to want to taste the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.81,0:44:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它会使你感到愉快\N{\rEng}It just feels so good. Tell me, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.15,0:44:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么是你童年中最不快乐的记忆?\N{\rEng}What is your worst memory of childhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.61,0:44:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你吓了我一大跳  -需要我帮忙吗?\N{\rEng}- Jesus, Starling! - Can I help you, Mr. Krendler?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.27,0:44:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个人坐在黑暗中干什么?\N{\rEng}What are you doing sitting there in the dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.35,0:44:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正想着吃人的问题\N{\rEng}Thinking about cannibalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.15,0:44:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司法部也在思索这个问题  你知道吗?\N{\rEng}People in Justice are thinking too. You know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.11,0:44:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在想 "她到底想对汉尼拔采取什么手段"\N{\rEng}They're thinking, " What exactly is she doing about Lecter?"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.22,0:44:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对他爱吃人是否感到好奇?\N{\rEng}Aren't you curious why he dines on his victims?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.69,0:44:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这话是什么意思?\N{\rEng}What's the point of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.98,0:44:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底是想写小说  还是想捉贼?\N{\rEng}Are you writing a book or are you catching a crook?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.07,0:44:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了报复那些侮辱他的人\N{\rEng}To show his contempt for those who exasperate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.64,0:44:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以他才偶尔充当刽子手\N{\rEng}Or sometimes to perform a public service.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.60,0:44:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就拿横笛手班哲明为例\N{\rEng}In the case of the flutist, Benjamin Raspail...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.27,0:44:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于他供应小牛胰脏和七百美金一瓶的蒙哈榭白酒\N{\rEng}he did it to improve the sound of the Baltimore Philharmonic Orchestra...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.60,0:45:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给乐团中那些没什么天份的横笛手享用\N{\rEng}serving the not-so-talented flute player's sweetbreads to the board...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.73,0:45:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因而使巴尔的摩交响乐团的声名大噪\N{\rEng}with a nice Montrachet at $700 a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.65,0:45:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哇!\N{\rEng}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.56,0:45:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那顿饭的开胃菜是产自法国隆特的牡蛎\N{\rEng}That meal began with green oysters from the Gironde...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.52,0:45:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接着是小牛胰脏  果汁奶冻\N{\rEng}followed by the sweetbreads, a sorbet...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.90,0:45:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他的你可以看这本美食杂志\N{\rEng}and then you can read here in Gourmet Cuisine:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.73,0:45:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"有名的黑且光泽的蔬菜炖肉  其中材料不明"\N{\rEng}"A notable dark and glossy ragout, the constituents never determined."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.77,0:45:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直认为他有同性恋\N{\rEng}I always figured him for a queer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.52,0:45:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么你会这么想?\N{\rEng}Why would you say that, Paul?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他搞的全是艺术方面的事\N{\rEng}All this artsy-fartsy stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.44,0:45:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像音乐室  茶会美食之类的  不是我多事...\N{\rEng}Chamber music, tea-party food. Not that I mean anything personal...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.48,0:45:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得你似乎很同情那种人\N{\rEng}if you've got a lot of sympathy for those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.60,0:45:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来这里是想让你明白\N{\rEng}What I came to impress upon you, Starling...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.44,0:45:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好乖乖合作\N{\rEng}is I better see cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.52,0:45:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这案子不是你一个人的\N{\rEng}There are no little fiefdoms here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.03,0:45:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你必须随时向我报告进展  懂吗?\N{\rEng}I want to be copied on every 302, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.10,0:45:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好和我合作\N{\rEng}If you work with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.07,0:45:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么你所谓的前途就会无量\N{\rEng}then your so-called career here might improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.61,0:46:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则  我不但不在你名字下划线\N{\rEng}If you don't, then all I have to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.86,0:46:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反而把线从你名字中间划过去\N{\rEng}is draw a line through your name rather than under it...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.36,0:46:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就前途无亮啦\N{\rEng}and it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.82,0:46:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底想怎么样?\N{\rEng}Paul, what is it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.31,0:46:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫你回到你太太身边去  难道错了吗?\N{\rEng}I told you to go home to your wife. That was wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.52,0:46:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托  你少自做多情了\N{\rEng}What? Don't flatter yourself, Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.78,0:46:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是几百年前的事\N{\rEng}That was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.52,0:46:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才不会记那么久的仇\N{\rEng}Why would I hold that against you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.94,0:46:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加上...\N{\rEng}And besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.11,0:46:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个城里到处都是种田的乡下女人\N{\rEng}this town is full of corn pone, country pussy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.40,0:46:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说...\N{\rEng}That said...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.27,0:46:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你愿意  我现在就能奉陪\N{\rEng}I wouldn't mind having a go with you right now, if you want to reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.48,0:46:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我随时在拳击场候教  来场不穿保护衣的对打\N{\rEng}In the gym, anytime. No pads.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.27,0:46:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会不会是用普通邮件送出的?\N{\rEng}Is it possible it went out with the regular mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.86,0:46:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会  是我亲手填的快递单\N{\rEng}No, I overnighted it to you. I filled out the slip myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.06,0:46:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且在你委托的第二天就寄了\N{\rEng}This was the day after your request.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.32,0:46:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我实在想不通\N{\rEng}I did it right away. I don't understand what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.53,0:46:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你现在该收到了\N{\rEng}You should have it by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.32,0:46:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还没有  能不能请你再寄一份\N{\rEng}I don't. Can you send me another one?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.69,0:47:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题  我会特别替你再录一份\N{\rEng}Sure, I'll make another copy especially for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.36,0:47:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是克莉丝探员吗?  我能叫你克莉丝吗?\N{\rEng}Agent Clarice? Is that right? Can I call you Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.20,0:47:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请叫我史达琳探员\N{\rEng}Agent Starling.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.66,0:47:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你的帮忙  请问贵姓?\N{\rEng}I'd appreciate it. What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.48,0:47:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫班尼帝\N{\rEng}My name is Franco Benetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.36,0:47:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,班尼帝探员\N{\rEng}Agent Franco Benetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.44,0:47:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-非常谢谢你  班尼帝探员  -不客气\N{\rEng}- Thank you very much, Agent Benetti. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.86,0:47:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那我明天就寄给你  -好的\N{\rEng}- So I'll send you tomorrow? - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.48,0:47:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}Bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.28,0:47:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是没有线索?\N{\rEng}Nothin', huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.49,0:47:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有  我还在等佛罗伦斯和伦敦的录影带\N{\rEng}Nothin' yet. Still waitin' on Florence and London.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.03,0:48:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你所拨的号码已停止使用\N{\rEng}The number you have dialed is not in service at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.49,0:48:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请检查所拨的号码...\N{\rEng}Please check the number...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.99,0:48:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么事?\N{\rEng}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.24,0:48:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有汉尼拔的消息\N{\rEng}I have information about Hannibal Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.20,0:48:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请问你是否和警方联络过?\N{\rEng}Have you shared your information with the police, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.03,0:48:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我鼓励你先这么做\N{\rEng}I'm required to encourage you to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.53,0:48:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在哪种情况下才会付悬赏金\N{\rEng}Is the reward payable under special circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.90,0:48:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我建议你在采取行动之前\N{\rEng}May I suggest you contact an attorney...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.40,0:48:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先和律师联络一下\N{\rEng}before taking any possibly illegal action?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.12,0:48:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在日内瓦有个律师  专精这种案件\N{\rEng}There's one in Geneva who's excellent in these matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.33,0:48:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以给你他的免费电话\N{\rEng}May I give you his toll-free number?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.40,0:49:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,号码是004123317\N{\rEng}The number is 004123317.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.58,0:49:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你打电话过来\N{\rEng}Thank you for calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.58,0:49:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人向我建议...\N{\rEng}Yes. I was just speaking with someone who suggested...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.74,0:49:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,预付金是十万美金\N{\rEng}There's a $ 100,000 advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.03,0:49:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了符合预付金的条件\N{\rEng}To qualify for the advance...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.12,0:49:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须先提供目标物的真实指纹\N{\rEng}a fingerprint must be provided, in situ, on an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.29,0:49:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等身份证实无误后\N{\rEng}Once the print has been positively identified...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.78,0:49:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即将余款存入瑞士银行\N{\rEng}the balance of the money will be placed in escrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.45,0:49:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,交由代书保管\N{\rEng}at Geneve Credit Suisse...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.37,0:49:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以随时检验  只要在24小时前通知即可\N{\rEng}and may be viewed at any time subject to 24-hour prior notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.91,0:49:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听法文请按二\N{\rEng}To repeat the message in French, press two.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.66,0:49:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西班牙文请按三  德文...\N{\rEng}In Spanish, press three. In German...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.41,0:50:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士  我是帕齐督察\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell, it's Inspector Pazzi.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.12,0:50:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  我看得见你\N{\rEng}Yes, I can see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.71,0:50:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请上来\N{\rEng}Come on up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.41,0:50:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士?\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.16,0:50:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士?\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.58,0:51:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士?\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.20,0:51:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,照张相\N{\rEng}Snap.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.50,0:51:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我应该嘱咐你多带个人来\N{\rEng}I should have encouraged you to bring someone along.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.04,0:51:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,箱子很重\N{\rEng}The cases are on the heavy side.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.12,0:51:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许要请你帮忙\N{\rEng}Maybe you could help me with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.83,0:51:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要搬到楼下就好\N{\rEng}Just down the stairs, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.33,0:51:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.24,0:51:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边走\N{\rEng}This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.12,0:51:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在这儿\N{\rEng}Here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.99,0:51:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那是清单吗?  -是的\N{\rEng}- Is that the inventory? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.79,0:51:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我能看吗?  -当然可以\N{\rEng}- May I see it? - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.46,0:52:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该是帕齐家族之后\N{\rEng}You are a Pazzi of the Pazzi family, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.87,0:52:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在维琪奥王宫被吊死的就是你的祖先\N{\rEng}Wasn't it at the Palazzo Vecchio your ancestor was hanged?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.42,0:52:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫范斯库·帕齐\N{\rEng}Francesco de' Pazzi.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.16,0:52:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,脖子上绑着套索  裸体从窗口中被抛出去\N{\rEng}Yes, thrown naked with a noose around his neck from a window.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.87,0:52:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在大主教的身边  碰撞着冰冷的墙壁\N{\rEng}Writhing and kicking alongside the archbishop...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.42,0:52:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全身扭动挣扎而死\N{\rEng}against the cold stone wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.49,0:52:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前几天  我在图书馆中\N{\rEng}In fact, I found a very nice rendering of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.71,0:52:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到了相关的艺术文献\N{\rEng}here in the library the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.54,0:52:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你喜欢  我可以偷偷给你\N{\rEng}If you like, perhaps I could sneak it out for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.62,0:52:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么做的话...\N{\rEng}I would think that might jeopardize your chances...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.46,0:52:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能会影响到你做馆长的机会\N{\rEng}for permanent appointment to the curatorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.54,0:52:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非你去告密\N{\rEng}Only if you told.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.91,0:52:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他到底犯了什么罪?\N{\rEng}Remind me... what was his crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.00,0:52:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他被控杀死朱利亚诺·梅迪奇\N{\rEng}He was accused of killing Giuliano de' Medici.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.84,0:52:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不公正吗?\N{\rEng}Unjustly?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.21,0:52:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  应该是公正的\N{\rEng}No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.04,0:53:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么说来  他是罪有应得\N{\rEng}Then he wasn't just accused. He did it. He was guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.08,0:53:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想就算在五百年后的今天\N{\rEng}I think that would make living in Florence with the name Pazzi...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.46,0:53:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你仍会为祖先的罪行而感到困扰\N{\rEng}uncomfortable, even 500 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.79,0:53:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这倒不会\N{\rEng}Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.00,0:53:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实在今天之前\N{\rEng}In fact, I can't remember the last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.55,0:53:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了你...\N{\rEng}before today...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.16,0:53:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根本就没人提过\N{\rEng}someone brought it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.12,0:53:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通常人们  不会把他的想法说出来\N{\rEng}People don't always tell you what they're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.79,0:53:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是会确实做到\N{\rEng}They just see to it you don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.13,0:53:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不让你出人头地而已\N{\rEng}advance in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.96,0:53:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起  请别介意\N{\rEng}I'm sorry, Commendatore.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.71,0:53:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我常想什么  就说什么\N{\rEng}I too often say what I'm thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.25,0:53:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我马上就回来帮你搬\N{\rEng}I'll be right back to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.67,0:54:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你所待的房间  是建造在十五世纪\N{\rEng}You know, the room you're standing in was built in the 15th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.63,0:54:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很美!\N{\rEng}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.59,0:54:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,的确不错\N{\rEng}Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.46,0:54:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只可惜  我在想...\N{\rEng}Unfortunately, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.75,0:54:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暖气系统  可能也是那时候建造的\N{\rEng}the heating system was installed about the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.96,0:54:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那真不幸  -的确\N{\rEng}- That's a pity. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.08,0:54:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  咱们把它们拿下去\N{\rEng}Okeydokey. Let's drag these down.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.17,0:54:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这大概和尸体一样重\N{\rEng}Must be as heavy as bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.34,0:55:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这一套多少钱?  -八千里拉\N{\rEng}- And the set? - Eight thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.05,0:55:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.29,0:55:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂  这个要多少钱?\N{\rEng}Hey, how much is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.34,0:55:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-五万里拉  -我买了\N{\rEng}- Fifty thousand. - I'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.46,0:55:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干得不错嘛\N{\rEng}Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.71,0:55:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你要偷他的皮夹时  他就会握住你的手腕\N{\rEng}When you go for his wallet, he'll catch you by the wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.55,0:55:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,督察  这种事我干过好几次\N{\rEng}I have done this a few times, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.72,0:55:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次不一样\N{\rEng}Not like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.54,0:56:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果手镯上没有清晰的指纹\N{\rEng}If there isn't a clean print on the bracelet...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.21,0:56:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么整个夏天  就请你到牢里去乘凉\N{\rEng}you'll spend the summer in a cell at the Sollicciano.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.76,0:56:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把手镯给我\N{\rEng}Give me the bracelet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.75,0:56:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先把你的脏手洗干净\N{\rEng}Wash your fucking hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.72,0:56:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他来啦\N{\rEng}He's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.10,0:58:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我弄到指纹了\N{\rEng}I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.18,0:58:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他正好握住手镯\N{\rEng}He grabbed me just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.23,0:58:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,居然想攻击我的下体\N{\rEng}Tried to hit me in the balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.76,0:58:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜没成功\N{\rEng}But he missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.84,0:58:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来帮你\N{\rEng}Let me help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.72,0:58:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要\N{\rEng}No. Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.31,0:59:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生  一共有十六处相符\N{\rEng}Sixteen-point match, Mr. Verger.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.56,0:59:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是他没错\N{\rEng}Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.26,0:59:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,撒丁尼亚岛
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.56,1:00:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是卡罗吗?  -维杰?\N{\rEng}- Carlo? - Mason?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.64,1:00:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都很好\N{\rEng}Well, well, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.23,1:00:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要我去你那儿吗?  -应该快了\N{\rEng}- Am I coming to see you? - Yes, soon, I hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.31,1:00:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过你先把野猪运过来\N{\rEng}But first I need you to pack off the boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.97,1:00:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-现在?  -是的  我知道\N{\rEng}- Now? - Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.14,1:00:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为这一天永远不会来  对不对?\N{\rEng}The day you never thought would arrive has.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.06,1:00:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德会直接把兽医表格\N{\rEng}Now, Cordell will fax the veterinary forms...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.68,1:00:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传真给动植物防疫检疫局\N{\rEng}directly to Animal and Plant Health...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.93,1:00:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你必须拿到撒丁尼亚岛的兽医检验表\N{\rEng}but you need to get the vet affidavits...from Sardinia.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.56,1:00:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们如何?\N{\rEng}How are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.18,1:00:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越长越大  非常庞大\N{\rEng}They are big, Mason, very big.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.73,1:00:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你再说一次  -它们长得很大\N{\rEng}- Say again? - Yeah, they are big, Mason.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.69,1:00:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大概有270公斤\N{\rEng}Really big. Maybe 270 kilos.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.65,1:00:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哇!  那么大\N{\rEng}Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.23,1:00:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听到了吗?\N{\rEng}Can you hear?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.15,1:01:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听起来很强壮\N{\rEng}They sound fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.40,1:01:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\N{\rEng}Super.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.56,1:02:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在收到活的汉尼拔医生后  余款就会全数付给你\N{\rEng}The full balance of the money is payable upon receipt of the doctor, alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.82,1:02:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该不会想自己去抓吧\N{\rEng}Of course, you won't have to seize him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.48,1:02:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要把他指认出来就行\N{\rEng}Rather, just point him out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.23,1:02:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其余的由我们来处理\N{\rEng}It's preferable to all concerned if that's the extent of your involvement...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.49,1:02:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样对你会比较好\N{\rEng}from this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.23,1:02:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望能一直参与下去  好确定不出问题\N{\rEng}I prefer to stay involved, make sure things go right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.40,1:02:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那将会由专家来执行\N{\rEng}Professionals will see to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.36,1:02:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是专家\N{\rEng}I am a professional.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.32,1:04:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,督察  你对这场演出满意吗?\N{\rEng}Did you enjoy the performance, Commendatore?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.91,1:04:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很满意\N{\rEng}Very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.91,1:04:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾葛莉  这位是费尔博士  卡波尼图书馆的馆长\N{\rEng}Allegra, this is Dr. Fell, curator of the Capponi Library.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.36,1:05:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕齐夫人\N{\rEng}Signora Pazzi.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.78,1:05:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很荣幸见到你\N{\rEng}I'm honored.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.78,1:05:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来自美国吗?\N{\rEng}Are you from America, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.78,1:05:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾到过美国  但祖籍不是那里\N{\rEng}Not originally. I've travelled there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.49,1:05:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直想去新英格兰\N{\rEng}I've always wanted to visit. New England, especially.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.61,1:05:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里的食物非常可口\N{\rEng}I've enjoyed many excellent meals there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.62,1:05:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我注意到你对歌词很有兴趣\N{\rEng}I noticed you wrapped up in the libretto.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.24,1:05:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信你会喜欢这个\N{\rEng}Thought this might amuse you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.28,1:05:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是但丁新生命中的  第一首十四行诗\N{\rEng}Dante's first sonnet from La Vita Nuova.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.28,1:05:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它非常美妙\N{\rEng}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.45,1:05:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-帕齐  你来看  -我看到了\N{\rEng}- Rinaldo, look at this. - I can see.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.95,1:05:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"对我来说喜悦的爱是"\N{\rEng}"Joyous Love seemed to me...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.29,1:05:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"当他手中捧着我的心"\N{\rEng}the while he held my heart in his hands...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.45,1:05:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"而在他臂弯中"\N{\rEng}and in his arms...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.28,1:05:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"却是我深爱的女士"\N{\rEng}my lady lay asleep...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.74,1:05:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"正裹着面纱沉睡着"\N{\rEng}wrapped in a veil."
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.66,1:05:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"然后他唤醒她"\N{\rEng}"He woke her then...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.99,1:05:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"她颤抖而顺从的  吃下他手中灼热的心"\N{\rEng}and trembling and obedient, she ate that burning heart out of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.87,1:05:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"我哽咽的看着他逐渐远去"\N{\rEng}Weeping, I saw him then depart from me."
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.83,1:06:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士  你相信男人  在第一次和女人相遇后\N{\rEng}Dr. Fell, do you believe a man could become so obsessed with a woman...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.12,1:06:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就会迷上她吗?\N{\rEng}from a single encounter?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.78,1:06:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他因此而寝食难安\N{\rEng}Could he daily feel a stab of hunger for her...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.79,1:06:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有在见到她后才能平静?\N{\rEng}and find nourishment in the very sight of her?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.78,1:06:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信\N{\rEng}I think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.07,1:06:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是她会看出他的苦境  而深深为他心痛吗?\N{\rEng}But would she see through the bars of his plight and ache for him?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.58,1:06:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这是送给你的  -我不能接受\N{\rEng}- Please keep that. - I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.95,1:06:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我坚持\N{\rEng}I insist.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.16,1:06:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,督察
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.33,1:06:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾葛莉
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.65,1:06:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再会
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.03,1:06:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}Good-bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.79,1:06:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们去吃点东西吧  -好的\N{\rEng}- Let's get something to eat. - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.79,1:06:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好主意\N{\rEng}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.29,1:06:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}暴戾罪犯的逮捕计划
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.53,1:06:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}登入系统者名单
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.53,1:06:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}50天内
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.16,1:07:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,医生  这会是你吗?\N{\rEng}Is that you, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.87,1:08:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请帕齐督察接电话\N{\rEng}I'd like to speak with Chief Inspector Rinaldo Pazzi, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.95,1:08:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是美国调查局探员史达琳\N{\rEng}This is Agent Clarice Starling from the American FBI.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.24,1:08:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请等一下\N{\rEng}One moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.12,1:08:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-FBI的电话  -说我不在\N{\rEng}- FBI. - I'm not here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.87,1:08:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是帕齐督察\N{\rEng}Inspector Pazzi.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.12,1:08:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是调查局的史达琳探员  你好?\N{\rEng}It's Agent Starling from the FBI. How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.04,1:08:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在正准备离开\N{\rEng}Actually, I was just leaving for the day.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.75,1:08:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-明天再和你联络好吗?  -不会耽误很久\N{\rEng}- Can I call you back tomorrow? - This won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.96,1:08:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首先  谢谢你们寄给我香水店的防盗录影带\N{\rEng}First, thank you for sending us the security tape from the perfume store.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.12,1:08:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我指的是  由班尼帝探员寄来的带子\N{\rEng}When I say "you,"I mean your department... Agent Benetti.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.83,1:08:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在吗?  我想和他谈谈\N{\rEng}Is he there? Can I speak with him?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.13,1:08:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-抱歉  他已经走了  -那没关系\N{\rEng}- I'm sorry. He's gone home. - That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.12,1:08:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我本就该对你说的\N{\rEng}I should tell you this rather than him anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.45,1:08:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有个重要约会就要迟到了\N{\rEng}I'm late for an important appointment.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.83,1:08:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我所要寻找的人\N{\rEng}The person I'm looking for, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.54,1:08:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就出现在那个录影带里  他的名字是汉尼拔\N{\rEng}who is indeed shown on that tape, is Hannibal Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.62,1:08:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁?\N{\rEng}Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.29,1:09:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生  你没听过他吗?\N{\rEng}Dr. Hannibal Lecter. You've never heard of him?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.29,1:09:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我不是很清楚  -录影带中显示\N{\rEng}- I'm not familiar. - And the tape confirms...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.13,1:09:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他曾在佛罗伦斯出现过\N{\rEng}that he is or was recently in Florence.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.41,1:09:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是吗?  -督察  他非常危险\N{\rEng}- Really? - He's a very dangerous man, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.50,1:09:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经杀害十四个人\N{\rEng}He's killed 14 people that we know of.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.95,1:09:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我得走了  你是...  -我叫史达琳\N{\rEng}- I really have to go, Miss... - Starling.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.37,1:09:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再给我一分钟\N{\rEng}Just another minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.12,1:09:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你确定没听过他吗?  -我确定\N{\rEng}- You sure you've never heard of him? - No, I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.13,1:09:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就奇怪了\N{\rEng}Because I'm confused.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.13,1:09:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为根据资料显示  你们有人时常使用电脑\N{\rEng}Someone there has been accessing our private VICAP files on Dr. Lecter...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.62,1:09:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从我们网站的VICAP档案中存取汉尼拔医生的资料\N{\rEng}with some regularity on your computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.71,1:09:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警局的电脑是公用的\N{\rEng}Everybody uses everybody's computer here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.70,1:09:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许是侦办莫斯楚的警探\N{\rEng}Maybe one of the detectives on II Mostro...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.71,1:09:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上网查看杀人魔的资料\N{\rEng}was looking at profiles of killers...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.75,1:09:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我所说的是你家里的电脑\N{\rEng}I'm speaking about the computer at your home, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.79,1:09:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是不是想自己去捉拿他  好拿悬赏金?\N{\rEng}You're trying to catch him yourself, aren't you? For the reward.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.33,1:09:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须警告你千万别这么做\N{\rEng}I cannot warn you strongly enough against that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.00,1:09:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当他在曼非斯被监管时  曾杀了三名警员\N{\rEng}He killed three policemen down in Memphis while in custody...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.96,1:09:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中之一的脸被他整个撕裂  他也会杀你的\N{\rEng}tearing the face off one of them, and he will kill you too.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.42,1:10:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我要他尽快离开此地  -相信我...\N{\rEng}- I want him out of Tuscany fast. - Believe me...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.87,1:10:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很快就会从地球上消失\N{\rEng}he'll be gone from the face of the earth fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.92,1:10:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到棺材里去休息\N{\rEng}Feetfirst.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.30,1:11:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于他的贪婪  背判了信任他的国王\N{\rEng}Because of his avarice and his betrayal of the emperor's trust...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.92,1:11:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使得韦格那遭到贬黜  失明和下狱之殃\N{\rEng}Pier della Vigna was disgraced, blinded and imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.25,1:11:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但丁神曲把他放在地狱篇的第七层地狱中\N{\rEng}Dante's pilgrim finds Pier della Vigna on the seventh level of the Inferno...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.92,1:11:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像耶稣的叛徒犹大一样  被处以绞刑\N{\rEng}and, likeJudas Iscariot, he died by hanging.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.46,1:11:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由此我们看出是贪婪\N{\rEng}SoJudas and Pier della Vigna are linked in Dante...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.38,1:11:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使但丁把他们俩连系起来\N{\rEng}by the avarice he saw in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.80,1:11:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上  在中世纪时  贪婪和绞刑常连为一体\N{\rEng}In fact, avarice and hanging are linked in the medieval mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.21,1:11:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最早的文献可见于西元400年  被刻在高卢的象牙盒上\N{\rEng}This is the earliest known depiction of the Crucifixion...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.67,1:11:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,记录着有关耶稣被钉死在十字架上的故事\N{\rEng}carved on an ivory box in Gaul about A.D. 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.04,1:11:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中包括绞杀犹大\N{\rEng}It includes the death by hanging ofJudas...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.96,1:11:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的脸孔朝上  面对着吊死他的树枝\N{\rEng}his face upturned to the branch that suspends him.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.97,1:11:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个在班尼文多大教堂门上的也是他\N{\rEng}Here he is again on the doors of the Benevento Cathedral...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.00,1:11:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不同的是  这里的他内脏外溢\N{\rEng}this time with his bowels falling out.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.00,1:12:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你听我说  我好不容易才要到你的号码\N{\rEng}It wasn't easy, but I got this number without tellin'them why...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.42,1:12:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-对不起  -没关系  欢迎你来\N{\rEng}- Sorry. - Not at all. Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.88,1:12:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-请坐  -谢谢你\N{\rEng}- Please join us. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.29,1:12:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这幅是十五世纪地狱篇的画\N{\rEng}On this plate from the 15th-century edition of the Inferno...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.30,1:12:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们看到韦格那的尸体  挂在流着鲜血的树上\N{\rEng}Pier della Vigna's body hangs from a bleeding tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.88,1:12:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想强调他和犹大的相似处\N{\rEng}I will not belabor the obvious parallel with Judas Iscariot...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.88,1:12:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为但丁已经描述得很清楚\N{\rEng}but Dante Alighieri needed no drawn illustration.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.88,1:12:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他技巧的表现出  韦格那仍在地狱之中\N{\rEng}It was his genius to make Pier della Vigna, now in hell...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.55,1:12:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,声嘶力竭的喊叫和挣扎\N{\rEng}speak in strained hisses and coughing sibilants...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.54,1:12:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像他仍被吊着一样\N{\rEng}as though he is hanging still.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.09,1:12:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贪婪  绞刑\N{\rEng}Avarice, hanging...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.50,1:12:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自我毁灭\N{\rEng}self-destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.47,1:13:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"绞架..."\N{\rEng}"I make my own home...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.75,1:13:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"就是我的家"\N{\rEng}be my gallows."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.13,1:13:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天到此为止  谢谢各位的光临\N{\rEng}Thank you, ladies and gentlemen, for your kind attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.26,1:13:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我虽然不是学者  但相信你一定能当上馆长\N{\rEng}I'm not a scholar, but I think you've got the job.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.47,1:13:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.80,1:13:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我能请你去喝杯酒吗?  -这是我的荣幸\N{\rEng}- May I buy you a drink? - How kind of you. I'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.80,1:13:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等我把东西收好就走\N{\rEng}I'll be a minute gathering my things.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.80,1:13:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢慢来\N{\rEng}Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.39,1:13:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾葛莉  我会晚点回家\N{\rEng}Allegra, I'll be home just a little later than I said.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.64,1:13:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和费尔博士去喝杯酒\N{\rEng}I'm taking Dr. Fell out for a drink.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.26,1:14:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到很多人走出来\N{\rEng}I can see the people coming out now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.64,1:14:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好  等会儿见  是我太太\N{\rEng}Yes. Bye, honey. My wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.38,1:14:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEng}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.43,1:14:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,刚才该给他们看这一张\N{\rEng}I should have shown them this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.18,1:14:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么会忘了  记得我曾对你说过吗?\N{\rEng}I can't imagine how I missed it. Remember? I told you about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.05,1:14:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我在图书馆里找到的\N{\rEng}It's a rendering I found in the Capponi Library.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.76,1:14:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能看得到吗?\N{\rEng}Can you make it out?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.60,1:14:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里有个名字\N{\rEng}There's a name there...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.42,1:14:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾对你提起过\N{\rEng}the one I told you about.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.51,1:14:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就是你的祖先\N{\rEng}It's your ancestor, Commendatore...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.72,1:14:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被吊死在这个窗子下面\N{\rEng}hanging beneath these very windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.38,1:14:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,范斯库·帕齐\N{\rEng}Francesco de' Pazzi.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.51,1:14:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另外我想向你坦白\N{\rEng}On a related subject, I must confess to you...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.18,1:14:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在认真的考虑\N{\rEng}I'm giving very serious thought...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.85,1:15:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿你太太当晚餐\N{\rEng}to eating your wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.14,1:15:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你能诚实回答我的问题\N{\rEng}If you tell me what I need to know, Commendatore...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.22,1:15:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许到时会放她一马\N{\rEng}it might be convenient for me to leave Florence without my meal.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.89,1:15:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我先来问你  然后再做决定  可以吗?\N{\rEng}So I'll ask you the questions, and then we'll see. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.55,1:15:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吗?\N{\rEng}Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.47,1:16:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}So.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.44,1:16:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把我出卖给维杰吗?\N{\rEng}Now, is it Mason Verger you sold me to?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.06,1:16:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别挣扎\N{\rEng}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.68,1:16:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是眨两次眼  不眨一次\N{\rEng}Blink twice for yes, once for no.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.98,1:16:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把我出卖给维杰吗?\N{\rEng}Was it Mason Verger you sold me to?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.14,1:16:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  很好  谢谢你\N{\rEng}Yes, good. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.14,1:16:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的人在外面等我吗?\N{\rEng}And are his men waiting for me outside?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.81,1:16:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是一下吗?\N{\rEng}Was that a single blink?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.97,1:16:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你搞混了\N{\rEng}You're confused.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.93,1:16:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别乱搅和  否则我真会把帕齐夫人的肉片下来吃\N{\rEng}Please don't be confused, because I may have to fillet Signora Pazzi after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.23,1:16:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你告诉过警局里的人吗?\N{\rEng}Have you told anyone in the questura about me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.22,1:16:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我也这么想\N{\rEng}No, I thought not.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.81,1:16:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有告诉过你太太?\N{\rEng}Have you told Allegra?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.35,1:16:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你确定\N{\rEng}No? Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.39,1:16:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信你\N{\rEng}I believe you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.64,1:16:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  咱们可以开始了\N{\rEng}Okeydokey, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.56,1:17:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.39,1:17:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的心抖得真厉害\N{\rEng}Your heart is really palpitating.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.06,1:17:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原来不是你的心\N{\rEng}Oh, it's not your heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.94,1:17:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能回答吗?\N{\rEng}Shall I answer it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.39,1:17:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经向你的局长说过了\N{\rEng}I've gone above you. I've spoken to your section chief.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.15,1:17:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将来你会谢我的  如果恨我  也无所谓\N{\rEng}Someday you'll thank me. Or you won't. I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.98,1:17:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少你还活着\N{\rEng}You'll be alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.39,1:17:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕齐督察?\N{\rEng}Inspector Pazzi?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.23,1:17:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是史达琳吗?\N{\rEng}Is this Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.60,1:17:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈罗  史达琳\N{\rEng}Hello, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.18,1:17:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,消息恐怕不太好\N{\rEng}I'm afraid I have bad news for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.14,1:17:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他死了吗?  -你收到我寄给你的信吗?\N{\rEng}- Is he dead? - Did you get my note?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.35,1:17:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你喜欢那瓶手霜  是我特别替你订制的\N{\rEng}I hope you like the skin cream. I had it specially made for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.11,1:17:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生  他死了吗?\N{\rEng}Is he dead, Dr. Lecter?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.11,1:17:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要知道  我最喜欢和你聊天\N{\rEng}I would love nothing more in this world than to be able to chat with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.31,1:17:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜现在实在不方便\N{\rEng}Unfortunately, you've caught me at an awkward moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.56,1:17:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请原谅我\N{\rEng}Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.90,1:17:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}See you around.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.89,1:18:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是个老朋友\N{\rEng}An old friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.90,1:18:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  别动\N{\rEng}Okay, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.19,1:18:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,咱们走吧\N{\rEng}Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.94,1:18:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我走后门  必要时杀了他\N{\rEng}I'll go around back! Kill him if you have to!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.27,1:18:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢哪样?\N{\rEng}What's it to be?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.32,1:18:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是内脏在里面  还是...\N{\rEng}Bowels in or bowels out...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.57,1:18:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像犹大一样流得满地都是\N{\rEng}like Judas?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.64,1:18:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道这又困扰你吗?\N{\rEng}Are you confused?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.56,1:19:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就由我来决定吧\N{\rEng}I'll decide for you, if you'll permit me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.82,1:19:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见啦
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.99,1:20:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在找我吗?\N{\rEng}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.91,1:20:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚安\N{\rEng}Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.49,1:21:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德\N{\rEng}Cordell...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.11,1:21:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,依你看...\N{\rEng}to you...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.11,1:21:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的招手是表示再会呢\N{\rEng}does that look like a wave good-bye...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.78,1:21:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是表示哈罗\N{\rEng}or hello?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.32,1:22:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是怎么想?\N{\rEng}So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.58,1:22:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到底汉尼拔是想和她睡觉  杀她还是吃她呢?\N{\rEng}Does Lecter want to fuck her or kill her or eat her or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.74,1:22:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许三者都是\N{\rEng}Probably all three.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.41,1:22:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是不知道是什么顺序\N{\rEng}Though I wouldn't want to predict in what order.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.62,1:22:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我的想法\N{\rEng}Here's what I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.28,1:22:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管巴尼加入多少浪漫的情节\N{\rEng}No matter how Barney might want to romanticize it...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.45,1:22:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他们描述得像美女与野兽一般\N{\rEng}and make it Beauty and the Beast...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.40,1:22:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,依我以前的经验来看\N{\rEng}Lecter's object, as I know from personal experience...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.66,1:22:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔的目的永远是\N{\rEng}has always been...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.95,1:22:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让人逐渐崩溃\N{\rEng}degradation...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.16,1:22:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且受尽痛苦\N{\rEng}and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.49,1:23:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把这该死的面具拿走  搞得我不能呼吸\N{\rEng}Get this damn thing off me. I can't breathe in this thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.83,1:23:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他常以良师益友的身份出现\N{\rEng}He comes in the guise of a mentor...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.07,1:23:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像当初他对我和她一样\N{\rEng}as he did with me and her.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.53,1:23:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,痛苦会使他兴奋\N{\rEng}But it's distress that excites him.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.58,1:23:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了要引出他来\N{\rEng}To draw him...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.82,1:23:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就必须要让她痛苦\N{\rEng}she needs to be distressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.04,1:23:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为  当他看到她痛苦时就会现身\N{\rEng}To make her attractive to him, let him see her distressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.53,1:23:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要他在看到她的痛苦后\N{\rEng}Let the damage he sees...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.20,1:23:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而忍不住去伤害她\N{\rEng}suggest the damage he could do.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.54,1:23:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像狐狸听到兔子悲鸣时  会跑过去吃掉它\N{\rEng}When the fox hears the rabbit scream, he comes a-runnin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.08,1:23:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不会去帮助它\N{\rEng}But not to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.16,1:23:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是我不懂\N{\rEng}I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.16,1:23:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗  你不需要懂\N{\rEng}There's nothing to understand, Paul.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.36,1:23:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要知道你能拿不少钱就行了\N{\rEng}All you have to understand is what it's worth to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.29,1:24:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是  我不懂  以她诚实的个性\N{\rEng}No, no, I don't understand why she didn't turn this over.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.29,1:24:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她应该会把它交出来的\N{\rEng}I mean, she's such a straight arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.33,1:24:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她没交出来  是因为没收到\N{\rEng}She didn't turn it over because she didn't receive it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.78,1:24:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她没收到  是因为没寄给她\N{\rEng}She didn't receive it because it was never sent.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.91,1:24:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没寄给她  是因为汉尼拔没写\N{\rEng}It was never sent because Lecter didn't write it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.41,1:24:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他没写  是因为那是我写的\N{\rEng}He didn't write it because I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.29,1:24:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为如何?\N{\rEng}So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.29,1:24:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得你最好别再帮她\N{\rEng}You'd have been better off if you'd never got her out of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.78,1:24:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你管得也太多了  我是问你要多少钱?\N{\rEng}Oh, woulda, shoulda, coulda. I meant, what do you think about the money?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.87,1:24:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五\N{\rEng}Five.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.12,1:24:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们为这个五干一杯\N{\rEng}Let's just toss it off, like "five."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.62,1:24:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你最好说清楚到底要多少\N{\rEng}Let's say it with the respect it deserves.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.66,1:24:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说五十万\N{\rEng}Five hundred thousand dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.71,1:24:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好  不多嘛\N{\rEng}That's better, but not much.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.67,1:24:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-能成功吗?  -绝对可以\N{\rEng}- Now, will it work? - It'll work.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.16,1:24:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜不会很好看\N{\rEng}It won't be pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.37,1:24:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那没关系\N{\rEng}What ever is?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.82,1:24:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白痴\N{\rEng}Cocksucker.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.08,1:25:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从没见过这东西\N{\rEng}Never seen this before in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.12,1:25:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那为什么会在地下室  你的办公室里找到呢?\N{\rEng}Then how do you account for its being found in your office, your basement?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.58,1:25:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要我怎么回答\N{\rEng}How do you want me to answer that, Mr. Krendler?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.58,1:25:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我根本没必要把它藏起来\N{\rEng}What possible reason might I have to withhold it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.58,1:25:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许是因为它的内容\N{\rEng}Perhaps because of the nature of its content.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.92,1:25:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,念起来倒像封情书\N{\rEng}Reads to me like a love letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.95,1:25:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有没有查过指纹  -没有指纹\N{\rEng}- Has it been tested for prints? - No prints on it. None on the last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.12,1:25:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,笔迹分析呢?\N{\rEng}Handwriting analysis?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.08,1:25:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"你有没有想过  为什么那些庸俗的人无法了解你"\N{\rEng}"Did you ever think, Clarice, why the philistines don't understand you?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.79,1:25:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"因为你就是参孙之谜"\N{\rEng}It's because you're the answer to Samson's riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.16,1:25:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"你是狮子里的蜜糖"\N{\rEng}You are the honey in the lion."
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.33,1:25:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很像他\N{\rEng}Sounds like him to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.92,1:25:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你是说像同性恋?  -我说像那个迷恋你的傻瓜\N{\rEng}- Do you mean, like a homosexual? - Like a nut with a crush.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.29,1:25:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,执政官诺门  我想说点...\N{\rEng}Director Noonan, I need to say something...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.70,1:25:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员  我命令你暂时停职\N{\rEng}Agent Starling, I am placing you on administrative leave...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.29,1:25:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到文件的分析  证明我们做出错误的决定为止\N{\rEng}till document analysis tells me unequivocally a mistake's been made.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.55,1:25:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在此期间  你仍能享用医疗保险\N{\rEng}In the meantime, you remain eligible for insurance and medical benefits.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.83,1:25:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你的武器和证件交给柏塞探员\N{\rEng}Surrender your weapons and your identification to Agent Pearsall.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.84,1:26:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有权力表达自己的想法\N{\rEng}I want to say something. I think I'm entitled.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.66,1:26:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请讲\N{\rEng}Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.50,1:26:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为  维杰先生为了私人恩怨\N{\rEng}I think Mr. Mason Verger is trying to capture Dr. Lecter...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.04,1:26:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要捉住汉尼拔医师\N{\rEng}for the purposes of personal revenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.13,1:26:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为保罗先生和他勾结\N{\rEng}I think Mr. Krendler is in collusion with him...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.70,1:26:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,利用调查局的资源  去帮助维杰先生\N{\rEng}and wants the FBI's efforts against Dr. Lecter to work for Mr. Verger.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.71,1:26:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我更认为保罗先生已被人收买\N{\rEng}I think Mr. Krendler is being paid to do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.67,1:26:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好在你今天没有发誓  -少吓我  你去发誓呀!\N{\rEng}- Lucky you're not sworn here today. - Swear me! You swear too!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.45,1:26:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  如果证据不足\N{\rEng}Clarice, if the evidence is lacking...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.29,1:26:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就能立即复职\N{\rEng}you'll be entitled to full reinstatement without prejudice...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.00,1:26:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你若采取不合作的态度\N{\rEng}if you don't do or say anything in the meantime...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.50,1:26:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就没希望了\N{\rEng}that would make that impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.21,1:26:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员在调查局任职十年\N{\rEng}Relieved of field duty pending an internal investigation...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.63,1:26:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今却被解除职务  等待内部调查\N{\rEng}Special Agent Clarice Starling, a ten-year veteran on the Bureau...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.66,1:26:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的事业始于\N{\rEng}began her career with an assignment...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.79,1:26:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与致命狂人汉尼拔的会晤\N{\rEng}to interview lethal madman Hannibal Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.96,1:26:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,早先  我们听到  司法部发言人保罗的评论\N{\rEng}Earlier, we heard comments from Justice Department spokesman Paul Krendler.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.91,1:26:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你评论一下  今早司法部所做的决定\N{\rEng}Can you comment on theJustice Department's decision this morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.25,1:27:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,调查局和司法部  都非常小心的处理此事\N{\rEng}The FBI and theJustice Department are looking very carefully into the charges.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.42,1:27:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且态度非常认真\N{\rEng}And, yes, they are extremely serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.83,1:27:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想加点自己的想法\N{\rEng}I'd like to add a personal note, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.42,1:27:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-史达琳是我们最好的探员之一  -不  你留下来\N{\rEng}- Starling's one of our best agents. - No, no, no, stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.13,1:27:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不相信这些控诉会成立\N{\rEng}I would be very surprised if these accusations turn out to be true.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.21,1:27:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道司法部和调查局  真的采取同一步调吗?\N{\rEng}Is theJustice Department and FBI united in this decision?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.75,1:27:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在还太早替她做结论\N{\rEng}It's much too soon to condemn her...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.09,1:28:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}佛利逊通讯
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.67,1:28:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乖狗\N{\rEng}Good boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.43,1:30:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得她很好\N{\rEng}I think she's nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.89,1:30:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她对我一直很好  很有礼貌\N{\rEng}She's always been nice to me. Polite.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.84,1:30:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你不同意\N{\rEng}Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.43,1:31:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼  你知道鹞鸽是什么吗?\N{\rEng}Do you know what a roller pigeon is, Barney?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.43,1:31:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鹞鸽喜欢飞得很高很快\N{\rEng}Roller pigeons climb high and fast...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.85,1:31:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后翻着筋斗快速冲向地面\N{\rEng}then roll over and fall just as fast towards the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.01,1:31:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鹞鸽又分成肤浅和深沉两种\N{\rEng}There are shallow rollers and there are deep rollers...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.43,1:31:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是当两个深沉的鹞鸽结合时\N{\rEng}but you can't breed two deep rollers, or their young, their offspring...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.93,1:31:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的后代往往会俯冲撞地而死\N{\rEng}will roll all the way down, hit and die.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.43,1:31:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳探员是只深沉的鹞鸽\N{\rEng}Agent Starling is a deep roller.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.51,1:31:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只希望她父母中有一个是肤浅的鹞鸽\N{\rEng}Let's hope one of her parents was not.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.60,1:32:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  电话的电池快用完了\N{\rEng}The power in that battery is low, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.10,1:32:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了不吵醒你  我没换\N{\rEng}I would've changed it, but I didn't want to wake you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.89,1:33:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以用充电器里的电池  但愿现在已经充好电了\N{\rEng}Use the one in the charger. Hopefully, the light on it is green by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.31,1:33:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这通电话会很长  而我又不愿意中途被切断\N{\rEng}Because this is gonna be a long call and I can't let you off...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.10,1:33:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更因为  他们虽然剥夺了你的职责\N{\rEng}because even though you've been stripped of your duties...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.60,1:33:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你一定会继续调查下去  绝不放弃\N{\rEng}I know you won't abandon them... you'll try to put on a trace.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.98,1:33:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们先挂断电话\N{\rEng}So we'll disconnect long enough for you to exchange the battery in the phone...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.68,1:33:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让你换电池\N{\rEng}for the one in the charger.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.77,1:33:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三秒钟够吗?\N{\rEng}Shall we say, three seconds?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.85,1:33:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-准备好了吗?  -好了\N{\rEng}- Are you ready? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.48,1:33:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开始\N{\rEng}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.98,1:33:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-很好  -谢谢你\N{\rEng}- Very good. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.94,1:33:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在哥伦比亚区  被抓到无照带枪\N{\rEng}Remember, Clarice, if you get caught with a concealed, unlicensed firearm...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.94,1:33:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,惩罚相当严重\N{\rEng}in the District of Columbia, the penalty is very stiff.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.85,1:33:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过如果你坚持那就带吧  现在到车里去\N{\rEng}But bring the guns if you have to. Now get in your car.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.39,1:34:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我之所以这么做\N{\rEng}The reason we're doing it like this, Clarice...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.73,1:34:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为当我们谈话时  我希望你是清醒的\N{\rEng}is because I like to watch you as we speak, with your eyes open.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.97,1:34:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别紧张  那不会使我兴奋  只会让我高兴而已\N{\rEng}No, it does not excite me. It pleases me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.69,1:34:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的脚形很美\N{\rEng}You have very shapely feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.27,1:34:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你现在在哪里?  把街名念出来\N{\rEng}Where are we now? Call it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.94,1:34:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,麻萨诸塞街\N{\rEng}Massachusetts Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.81,1:34:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到麻萨诸塞街去\N{\rEng}Take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.77,1:34:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们就拿你的感受做开场吧\N{\rEng}I thought, to begin with, you might tell me how you're feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.64,1:34:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那方面的?\N{\rEng}About what?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.68,1:34:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,例如你雇主如何对待你\N{\rEng}The masters you serve and how they've treated you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.65,1:34:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有你的职业\N{\rEng}Your career, such as it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.44,1:34:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至你的生命...\N{\rEng}Your life, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.40,1:34:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为会谈你的事\N{\rEng}I thought we might talk about yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.43,1:34:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-下面的横街叫什么?  -国会街\N{\rEng}- What's the next cross street? - Capitol Street.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.52,1:35:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在第二条街左转  把车停到火车站去\N{\rEng}In two blocks, make a left into Union Station. Park.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.07,1:35:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的生命?  那有什么好谈\N{\rEng}My life? What is there to say about mine?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.56,1:35:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已冬眠了一段日子\N{\rEng}I have been in a state of hibernation for some time...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.73,1:35:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乏善可陈\N{\rEng}a little inactive.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.90,1:35:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是现在我回来了  既快乐又健康\N{\rEng}But now I'm back home and I'm very happy...and very healthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.06,1:35:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-倒是你让我很操心  -我很好\N{\rEng}- You. It's you I'm worried about. - I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.52,1:35:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你一点也不好\N{\rEng}No, you're certainly not fine, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.39,1:35:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把自己奉献给调查局\N{\rEng}You fell in love with the Bureau, the institution...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.19,1:35:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而在付出一切之后\N{\rEng}only to discover, after giving it everything you've got...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.65,1:35:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却发现他们并不喜欢你\N{\rEng}that it does not love you back...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.82,1:35:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这点让你愤愤不平\N{\rEng}that, in fact, it resents you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.89,1:35:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比放弃丈夫和孩子还要愤怒\N{\rEng}It resents you more than the husband and children you gave up to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.94,1:35:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么?  为什么你会这么愤怒\N{\rEng}Why is that, do you think? Why are you so resented?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.48,1:35:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你告诉我  -我告诉你?\N{\rEng}- Tell me. - Tell you?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.02,1:35:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝会保祐你\N{\rEng}God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.73,1:35:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你难道还看不出来\N{\rEng}Well, isn't it clear?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.36,1:35:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听命行事\N{\rEng}You serve the idea of order, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.86,1:35:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不是\N{\rEng}They don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.31,1:35:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你遵守宣誓  他们不是\N{\rEng}You believe in the oath you took. They don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.98,1:36:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得保护弱小是你的责任  他们不是\N{\rEng}You feel it is your duty to protect the sheep. They don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.45,1:36:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你的不同  所以他们不喜欢你\N{\rEng}They don't like you because you're not like them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.65,1:36:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们对你又妒又恨\N{\rEng}They hate you and envy you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.94,1:36:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们懦弱  任性  又无法无天\N{\rEng}They are weak, unruly and believe in nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.28,1:36:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}快速照相
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.78,1:36:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生  维杰要杀你\N{\rEng}Mason Verger wants to kill you, Dr. Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.39,1:36:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向我投降  我保证没人会伤害你\N{\rEng}Turn yourself in to me, and I promise no one will hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.23,1:36:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会握着我的手  和我一起待在监狱里吗?\N{\rEng}Will you stay with me in my prison cell and hold my hand, Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.86,1:36:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那样一定很有意思\N{\rEng}We could have some fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.28,1:36:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你错了  其实我更想杀维杰\N{\rEng}No, Mason Verger does not want to kill me any more than I want to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.81,1:36:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只想用不可思议的方法来折磨我\N{\rEng}He just wants to see me suffer in some unimaginable way.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.82,1:36:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是个无可救药的疯子\N{\rEng}He is rather twisted, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.03,1:36:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你见过他吗?  -见过\N{\rEng}- Have you had the pleasure of meeting him? - I have
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.56,1:36:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,面对面?\N{\rEng}Face-to-face, so to speak?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.86,1:36:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.86,1:36:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他是不是很引人注意?  -汉尼拔医生\N{\rEng}- Attractive, isn't he? - Dr. Lecter?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.35,1:36:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在哪里?\N{\rEng}Dr. Lecter?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.44,1:36:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  再回来谈你\N{\rEng}Okay, back to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.53,1:36:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今所有你关心的东西\N{\rEng}I want to know what it is you think you will do...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.86,1:36:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全被他们拿走了  我想知道你打算怎么办\N{\rEng}now that everything you've ever cared about has been taken away from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.27,1:36:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know, Dr. Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.78,1:37:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能像你妈妈一样\N{\rEng}Clarice, do you think you'll work as a chambermaid...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.70,1:37:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到汽车旅馆里去\N{\rEng}at a motel on Route 66...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.53,1:37:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当打扫女工吗?\N{\rEng}just like your mommy?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.48,1:37:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在想什么?\N{\rEng}What are you thinking now?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.65,1:37:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卸任的史达琳探员  你在听我说话吗?\N{\rEng}Are you paying attention to me, ex-Special Agent Starling?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.53,1:37:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是想找出我的藏身处\N{\rEng}Are you, by any chance, trying to trace my whereabouts?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.90,1:37:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-汉尼拔医生  我被跟踪了  -我已经看到他们\N{\rEng}- I'm being followed, Dr. Lecter. - I know. I've seen them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.45,1:37:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你现在真是左右为难\N{\rEng}And now you're in a real dilemma, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.40,1:37:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明知会引导他们找到我  难道你还要继续找吗?\N{\rEng}Do you continue to try to find me, knowing that you are leading them to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.32,1:37:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是你认为  自己真有能力\N{\rEng}Do you have so much faith in your abilities that you honestly believe...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.02,1:37:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能同时逮捕我们双方\N{\rEng}you can somehow simultaneously arrest me and them?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.94,1:37:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过结果可能会和  鲜鱼市场一样糟糕\N{\rEng}It could get very messy, Clarice, like the fish market.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.62,1:37:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-让我来替你做如何?  -做什么?\N{\rEng}- What if I did it for you? - Did what?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.36,1:37:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伤害那些伤害过你的人\N{\rEng}Harmed them, Clarice, the ones who have harmed you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.99,1:38:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫他们来求你的原谅\N{\rEng}What if I made them scream apologies?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.37,1:38:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我真不该说\N{\rEng}No, I shouldn't even say it...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.44,1:38:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为若以你的是非标准来衡量\N{\rEng}because you'll feel, with your perfect grasp of right and wrong...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.90,1:38:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕会认为自己也是共犯\N{\rEng}that you were somehow accompli.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.45,1:38:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别帮我\N{\rEng}Don't help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.44,1:38:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然不会  忘了我所说的\N{\rEng}No, of course not. Forget I said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.41,1:38:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你很接近目标\N{\rEng}Clarice, you were very, very warm.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.28,1:38:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常接近\N{\rEng}You were so close.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.49,1:38:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在又偏了\N{\rEng}And now you're getting colder again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.48,1:38:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对  就是这儿\N{\rEng}Yeah, warmer again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.78,1:38:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好啦  给你的提示已经够多了\N{\rEng}Well, I think I've been generous enough with you and the clues.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.03,1:38:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你自己去找吧  -汉尼拔医生\N{\rEng}- You're on your own now, Clarice. - Dr. Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.79,1:38:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你喜欢它们  回见\N{\rEng}Hope you like them, Clarice. Ta-ta.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.41,1:39:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放进去\N{\rEng}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.49,1:39:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别挡住我!\N{\rEng}Get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.99,1:40:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道歇斯底里人的第一句话  是"我没有歇斯底里"\N{\rEng}I know the first thing a hysteric says is, "I am not a hysteric"...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.91,1:40:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我很镇静没有歇斯底里\N{\rEng}but I am not a hysteric. I am calm.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.28,1:40:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再问你一次  先想过再回答\N{\rEng}I'll ask you one time. Think before you answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.41,1:40:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想你以前的优良事迹\N{\rEng}Think about every good thing you ever did.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.45,1:40:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想你的宣誓\N{\rEng}Think about what you swore.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.41,1:40:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有两个人在货车里  第三个开车  另一个倒地不起\N{\rEng}Two men in a van, a third driving, another man down.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.78,1:40:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们把他放在后面  我想是汉尼拔\N{\rEng}They put him in the back. I think it was Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.41,1:40:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我给你车牌号码  并且会在目击者面前再向你报告一次\N{\rEng}I gave you a license, and I'm reporting it to you again in front of witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.82,1:40:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\rEng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.58,1:40:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我将以绑架来处理\N{\rEng}I'll go with it as a kidnapping.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.24,1:40:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会派人和当地警员前往\N{\rEng}I'll send someone with the local authorities...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.41,1:40:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望他们不会要我们出示搜索状\N{\rEng}if they'll let us on the property without a warrant.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.78,1:40:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我也去  你可以指定我为代表  -不行  你不能去\N{\rEng}- I should go. You could deputize me. - No. You're not going.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.20,1:40:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该回家等我电话\N{\rEng}You're going home, where you'll wait for me to call...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.96,1:40:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如有发现我会马上告诉你\N{\rEng}and tell you what, if anything, we've found.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.95,1:40:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢维杰先生让我们查看  若有打扰的地方请原谅\N{\rEng}Thank Mr. Verger for letting us look around. Sorry if we inconvenienced him.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.33,1:40:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放心  他随时都欢迎你们\N{\rEng}He's always happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.00,1:41:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要打电话\N{\rEng}Phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.11,1:41:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么号码\N{\rEng}What number, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.78,1:41:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接卡罗\N{\rEng}Carlo.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.95,1:41:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给我一杯\N{\rEng}Give me one.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.12,1:41:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他怎么样?  -在睡觉\N{\rEng}- How is he? - Sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.66,1:41:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他带回家吧\N{\rEng}Bring him home.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.46,1:41:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是史达琳  请留话\N{\rEng}You've reached Clarice Starling. Please leave a message.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.99,1:41:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  接电话\N{\rEng}Pick up, Starling.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.62,1:41:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里一切正常\N{\rEng}There was nothing out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.66,1:42:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再重复一遍\N{\rEng}I'm gonna say it again, in case you didn't hear me.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.17,1:42:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你被停职时  就是普通百姓  而不是执法警官\N{\rEng}You are not a law officer while you're on suspension. You'reJoe Blow.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.24,1:42:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了你好  希望你正在洗澡\N{\rEng}Hope for your sake you're in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.37,1:42:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的...\N{\rEng}Hylochoerus...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.08,1:42:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丛林猪\N{\rEng}meinertzhageni.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.34,1:42:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高中的生物学中曾经提过  你还记得吗?\N{\rEng}Ring any bells from high school biology, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.50,1:42:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不记得了?\N{\rEng}No?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.50,1:43:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我把它的特征告诉你\N{\rEng}Well, I could list its most conspicuous features...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.17,1:43:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许会唤起你的记忆\N{\rEng}if that would help jog the memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.66,1:43:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有三对门牙\N{\rEng}Three pairs of incisors...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.67,1:43:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一对延长犬齿\N{\rEng}one pair of elongated canines...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.75,1:43:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三对臼齿\N{\rEng}three pairs of molars...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.17,1:43:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四对前臼齿\N{\rEng}four pairs of premolars...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.80,1:43:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上下加起来\N{\rEng}upper and lower...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.16,1:43:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一共四十四颗牙\N{\rEng}for a total of 44 teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.87,1:43:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们正餐前的开胃菜\N{\rEng}The meal will begin with an hors d'oeuvres tartare...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.21,1:43:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是生吃人脚\N{\rEng}your feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.01,1:43:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主菜当然是少了一双脚的你\N{\rEng}The main course... the rest of you...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.08,1:43:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过得在七个钟头后才开饭\N{\rEng}won't be served until seven hours later.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.84,1:43:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在那段时间里\N{\rEng}But during that time...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.17,1:43:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会为你全身会打满点滴\N{\rEng}you'll be able to enjoy the effects of the consumed appetizer...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.67,1:43:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让你能清醒的感觉到  被生吃的痛楚\N{\rEng}with a full-bodied saline drip.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.13,1:44:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我打赌你正在想\N{\rEng}I guess you wish now...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.46,1:44:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当初真该把我喂狗吃\N{\rEng}you'd fed the rest of me to the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.50,1:44:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会的\N{\rEng}No, Mason.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.13,1:44:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢你现在这样\N{\rEng}No, I much prefer you the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.79,1:44:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么...\N{\rEng}So...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.92,1:44:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚餐就订在八点\N{\rEng}dinner at 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.67,1:44:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  今晚的娱乐活动\N{\rEng}You will stay for the evening's entertainment...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.38,1:44:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会参加吧?\N{\rEng}won't you, Cordell?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.22,1:44:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不介意\N{\rEng}If it's all right with you...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.88,1:44:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我宁可不想参加\N{\rEng}I think I'd rather not.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.71,1:45:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是宁可不\N{\rEng}Rather not...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.97,1:45:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是宁愿不?\N{\rEng}or will not?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.47,1:47:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你弟弟现在的味道  一定和你一样难闻\N{\rEng}Your little brother must smell almost as badly as you do by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.35,1:47:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不准动  手举起来\N{\rEng}Hold it! Hands where I can see 'em!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.43,1:47:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,闭嘴\N{\rEng}Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.35,1:47:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么声音?\N{\rEng}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.97,1:47:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  快一点\N{\rEng}Cordell, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.30,1:48:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,趴下来\N{\rEng}Get on your stomach.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.47,1:48:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  晚安\N{\rEng}Good evening, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.14,1:48:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-像又回到往日一样  -闭嘴\N{\rEng}- Just like old times. - Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.01,1:48:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你能走吗?  -我会尽力\N{\rEng}- Can you walk? - I can try.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.35,1:48:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看起来不错\N{\rEng}You look well.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.93,1:48:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在给你松绑\N{\rEng}I'm gonna cut you loose.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.05,1:48:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别碰我  否则我马上开枪\N{\rEng}If you touch me, I'll shoot you.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.35,1:48:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我了解  -不捣蛋你就能活着出去\N{\rEng}- Understood. - Do right and you'll live through this.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.64,1:48:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,语气和新教徒一样  最好快点\N{\rEng}Spoken like a true Protestant. Better hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.68,1:48:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把刀给我会快一点\N{\rEng}Things might go faster if you hand me the knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.18,1:48:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第三个人在阁楼上\N{\rEng}There was a third in the loft.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.72,1:48:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  是我后面\N{\rEng}No, Clarice. Behind me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.02,1:49:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  杀他  拿起枪  把他杀了\N{\rEng}Cordell, shoot him! Get the gun and shoot him!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.80,1:49:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-到围栏里去  -当然!\N{\rEng}- Go into the pen? - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.31,1:49:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我不要牵扯进去\N{\rEng}No. I'm staying out of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.64,1:49:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样  你已经扯进来了  快去\N{\rEng}You're involved, is what you are, in all of it. Now do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.72,1:49:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不  -你快去!\N{\rEng}- No. - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.85,1:49:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德  干脆把他推进去\N{\rEng}Hey, Cordell, why don't you push him in?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.02,1:49:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时推到我头上就行了\N{\rEng}You can always say it was me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.72,1:49:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德\N{\rEng}Cordell
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.85,1:49:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德?\N{\rEng}Cordell
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.31,1:49:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德!\N{\rEng}Cordell
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.39,1:49:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德!\N{\rEng}Cordell
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.44,1:51:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛莉  是我\N{\rEng}Mary, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.11,1:51:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我决定提前下班  周末到湖边去住\N{\rEng}I decided to take off early. I'll be at my lake house all weekend.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.86,1:51:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别把电话接过去  你听清楚了吗?\N{\rEng}I don't want any calls forwarded either. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.64,1:51:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管谁都让他们等  懂吗?\N{\rEng}Whoever it is, they can all wait. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:28.48,1:51:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托这是国庆假日呀  谢谢你\N{\rEng}Listen, it's 4th ofJuly, for Christ's sake. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.06,1:51:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么搞的?\N{\rEng}What the fuck?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.11,1:52:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好  你带酒来了\N{\rEng}Good. You brought the wine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.40,1:53:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一次我手里拿着  点燃的爆竹和朋友打赌\N{\rEng}One time I bet a friend I could hold a lit firecracker in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.11,1:53:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赌我能拿得比他久\N{\rEng}longer than he could.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.95,1:53:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你猜结果如何?\N{\rEng}Can I guess?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.15,1:53:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你输了赌注  他丢了手指头  对不对?\N{\rEng}You lost the bet, and he lost a finger. Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.19,1:53:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放心  不会痛的\N{\rEng}This won't hurt a bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.82,1:53:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有客人要来吗?\N{\rEng}Are we expecting guests?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.32,1:54:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经追踪到电话  警方在十分钟内会到达\N{\rEng}We've traced your call and units will be there in about ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.82,1:54:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你能到屋外去最好\N{\rEng}If you can do it safely, just get out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.15,1:54:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则就继续和我通话\N{\rEng}Otherwise, stay on the phone with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.49,1:54:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小姐?\N{\rEng}Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.98,1:54:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小姐  你仍在线上吗?\N{\rEng}Are you there? Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.08,1:54:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你必须让客人觉得温暖\N{\rEng}You need to make sure they feel welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.49,1:55:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那是冬葱吗?  -还有续随子香料\N{\rEng}- Are those shallots? - And caper berries.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.15,1:55:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奶油闻起来好香\N{\rEng}That butter smells wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.45,1:55:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗  你饿了吗?\N{\rEng}You feeling hungry, Paul?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.74,1:55:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好饿\N{\rEng}Very.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.91,1:55:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主菜是什么?\N{\rEng}What's the main course?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.37,1:55:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不该问  那样就没有惊喜了\N{\rEng}You should never ask. It spoils the surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.99,1:55:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  你起来干什么?  你应该休息  快回床上去\N{\rEng}Clarice, what are you doing up? You should be resting. Get back to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.91,1:55:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我饿了\N{\rEng}I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.49,1:55:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-哈罗  保罗  -保罗  要有礼貌\N{\rEng}- Hello, Paul. - Paul, don't be rude.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.49,1:55:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说 "哈罗  史达琳探员"\N{\rEng}Say, "Hello, Agent Starling."
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.58,1:55:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈罗  史达琳探员\N{\rEng}Hello, Agent Starling.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.82,1:55:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直想看你吃饭\N{\rEng}I always wanted to watch you eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.91,1:55:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你手里拿着什么  是想拿来砸我的头吗?\N{\rEng}What have you got in your hand? Something to bash me on the head with?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.82,1:55:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把它放在桌子上\N{\rEng}Put it on the table.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.41,1:55:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乖孩子\N{\rEng}Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.82,1:56:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿  那是我的\N{\rEng}Hey. That's mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.16,1:56:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下来\N{\rEng}Now sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.15,1:56:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  我喜欢你的衣服\N{\rEng}Hey, Clarice, love the dress.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.16,1:56:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很漂亮\N{\rEng}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.33,1:56:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-保罗  你说呢?  -好\N{\rEng}- What do you think, Paul? - Nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.65,1:56:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\N{\rEng}Nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.65,1:56:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗  由你来说饭前祈祷文好吗?\N{\rEng}Why don't you say grace, Paul?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.16,1:56:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我?  -是的\N{\rEng}- Me? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.66,1:56:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-祈祷文?  -没错\N{\rEng}- Grace? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.25,1:56:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.28,1:56:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把头低下来\N{\rEng}Bow your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.33,1:56:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天父  感谢你赐给我们食物\N{\rEng}Father, we thank Thee for Thy blessings...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:41.33,1:56:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及你对他们的慈悲\N{\rEng}and dedicate them to Thy mercy...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.32,1:56:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将要接受圣餐\N{\rEng}We are about to receive...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.57,1:56:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请饶恕我们大家\N{\rEng}Forgive us all...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.33,1:56:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也饶恕史达琳这种穷白鬼\N{\rEng}even white trash like Starling here...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.50,1:56:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并让她替我服务  阿门\N{\rEng}and bring her into my service, amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.62,1:56:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须告诉你  即使是基督的门徒保罗  说得也没你好\N{\rEng}I have to tell you, Paul, even the Apostle Paul couldn't have done better.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.00,1:57:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也讨厌女人\N{\rEng}He hated women too.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.16,1:57:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我能喝点酒吗?  -恐怕不好\N{\rEng}- May I have some wine, please? - I don't think that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.70,1:57:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你身上还有吗啡\N{\rEng}Not with the morphine.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.45,1:57:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你最好喝点汤\N{\rEng}I think you should eat some broth. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.00,1:57:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便告诉你  祈祷文里有你的工作机会\N{\rEng}By the way, that was a job offering I worked into the blessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.07,1:57:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我想进军众议院\N{\rEng}I'm going to Congress, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.16,1:57:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗?\N{\rEng}Are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:18.95,1:57:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到我的竞选总部来\N{\rEng}Come around campaign headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:21.83,1:57:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以做办公小姐  你会打字和存档吗?\N{\rEng}You could be an office girl. Can you type and file?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.41,1:57:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会速记吗?  把这个记下来\N{\rEng}Can you take dictation? Take this down.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.20,1:57:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,华盛顿充满了种田的乡下女人\N{\rEng}Washington is full of corn pone, country pussy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.99,1:57:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经记下来  你早先说过了\N{\rEng}I took it down. You said it already.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.83,1:57:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗  你变得很无礼  我讨厌无礼的家伙\N{\rEng}Paul, now you're being rude, and I hate rude people.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.21,1:57:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乖孩子  先喝汤  来  吸一口\N{\rEng}Drink your broth like a good boy. Come on. Sip.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.12,1:57:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:51.92,1:57:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老兄呀  实在不好喝\N{\rEng}It's not very good, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.58,1:57:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我加了点其他作料  可能和茴香的香味不调合\N{\rEng}I admit I added something to yours. Perhaps it's clashing with the cumin.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.62,1:58:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是保证你会爱死下道菜\N{\rEng}But I assure you, the next course is to die for.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:13.03,1:58:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别这样\N{\rEng}Come on, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.08,1:58:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这才乖\N{\rEng}That's a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:17.25,1:58:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.08,1:58:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生\N{\rEng}Dr. Lecter.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.25,1:58:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不用担心  其实脑本身没有痛楚感\N{\rEng}You see, the brain itself feels no pain, Clarice, if that concerns you.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.41,1:58:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,例如这是前头叶\N{\rEng}For example, Paul won't miss this little piece here...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:59.25,1:59:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算保罗少了它也没有关系\N{\rEng}part of the prefrontal lobe...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:01.25,1:59:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为据说  它能使人有良好的态度\N{\rEng}which they say is the seat of good manners.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:04.41,1:59:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的档案在边界警局中  有五个重点\N{\rEng}Your profile at the border stations has five features.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.21,1:59:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我和你交换  -交换?\N{\rEng}- I'll trade you. - Trade?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.91,1:59:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放了他  我就告诉你那些资料\N{\rEng}Stop, and I'll tell you what they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:11.95,1:59:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对交换两个字有什么感觉\N{\rEng}How does that word taste to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:14.83,1:59:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又冷又硬  就像在啜一枚油腻的硬币似的\N{\rEng}Cheap and metallic, like sucking on a greasy coin?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.96,1:59:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谁是克莉丝?  -就是史达琳探员\N{\rEng}- Who's Clarice? - Agent Starling, Paul.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.00,1:59:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你跟不上就别打岔\N{\rEng}If you can't keep up with the conversation, try not to join in at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:24.54,1:59:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗  我就是史达琳\N{\rEng}Paul, I'm Starling.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.71,1:59:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看...\N{\rEng}See...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.71,1:59:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在这里...\N{\rEng}here...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:30.71,1:59:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,脑子就在这个液囊之中\N{\rEng}right here's the sac that contains the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:36.92,1:59:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我真的需要喝点酒\N{\rEng}I would really like some wine.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.91,1:59:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好好闻哟  -没错\N{\rEng}- That smells great. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:45.41,1:59:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  要试一小块吗?\N{\rEng}There. Like to try a little piece?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:48.63,1:59:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是真的要喝点酒\N{\rEng}I would really like some wine...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.20,1:59:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好吃\N{\rEng}It is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:56.04,1:59:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  不过只能喝一点\N{\rEng}All right. Just a little.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.21,2:00:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喝吧\N{\rEng}Okay?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:19.59,2:00:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要有机会  你连我的命都会要  对不对?\N{\rEng}Given the chance, you would deny me my life, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:23.75,2:00:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是你的命\N{\rEng}Not your life.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:25.54,2:00:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是自由咯  你要把我的自由拿走\N{\rEng}My freedom, just that. You'd take that from me.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.71,2:00:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算你这么做  他们会要你回去吗?\N{\rEng}And if you did, would they have you back, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:32.17,2:00:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说调查局\N{\rEng}The FBI?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:34.79,2:00:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你蔑视的人同样也轻视你\N{\rEng}Those people you despise almost as much as they despise you?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:38.34,2:00:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想他们会给你奖章吗?\N{\rEng}Will they give you a medal, Clarice, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.59,2:00:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后你把它装框挂在墙上\N{\rEng}Would you have it professionally framed and hang it on your wall to look at...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:45.00,2:00:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天看着它  提醒自己有多勇敢和清廉吗?\N{\rEng}and remind you of your courage and incorruptibility?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:52.01,2:00:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,果真如此  一面镜子就够了\N{\rEng}All you would need for that, Clarice, is a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:57.04,2:01:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伶牙俐齿的人我另有用处  我永远不会再雇用你\N{\rEng}I have plans for that smart mouth. I'm never gonna hire you now.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:06.63,2:01:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗  我告诉过你\N{\rEng}Remember what I said?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:08.50,2:01:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果对客人不礼貌\N{\rEng}If you can't be polite to our guests...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.42,2:01:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就要到小孩桌去坐\N{\rEng}you have to sit at the kiddies' table.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.17,2:01:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  你别起来\N{\rEng}Don't get up, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:17.50,2:01:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗会帮我收拾和煮咖啡\N{\rEng}Paul will help me clear and make the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:23.25,2:01:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你仔细想想我说的话\N{\rEng}Just think about what I said, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:27.46,2:01:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,咖啡\N{\rEng}Coffee.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.13,2:02:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我绕了半个地球\N{\rEng}I came halfway around the world...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:09.67,2:02:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就为了看你如何释放自己\N{\rEng}to watch you run, Clarice.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:14.54,2:02:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,释放我  好吗?\N{\rEng}Let me run, huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:35.67,2:02:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  会不会有一天你对我说...\N{\rEng}Tell me, Clarice, would you ever say to me...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:40.18,2:02:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"别这么做"\N{\rEng}"Stop.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:41.80,2:02:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"如果爱我  就别这么做"\N{\rEng}If you loved me, you'd stop"?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.55,2:02:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永远不会\N{\rEng}Not in a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:49.34,2:02:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好个永远不会\N{\rEng}Not in a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:57.01,2:02:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就欣赏你这点\N{\rEng}That's my girl.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:12.67,2:03:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达琳  我必须承认你不简单\N{\rEng}Now, that's really interesting, Clarice...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:16.42,2:03:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我的时间又很紧迫\N{\rEng}and I'm really pressed for time.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:18.51,2:03:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我钥匙在哪里\N{\rEng}So where's the key?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:22.31,2:03:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,钥匙呢?\N{\rEng}Where's the key?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:30.05,2:03:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:36.51,2:03:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要切在...\N{\rEng}Above...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.01,2:03:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,手腕的上面...\N{\rEng}or below the wrist...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:39.89,2:03:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是下面?\N{\rEng}Clarice?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:49.10,2:03:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次绝对会很疼\N{\rEng}This is really gonna hurt.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:40.68,2:04:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把手举起来\N{\rEng}Show me your hands!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:43.38,2:04:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说明你的身份\N{\rEng}Identify yourself!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:46.01,2:04:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是克莉丝·史达琳\N{\rEng}I'm Clarice Starling!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:48.93,2:04:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,调查局探员\N{\rEng}FBI!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:49.93,2:05:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-嗨  -嗨\N{\rEng}- Hi. - Hi.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:51.73,2:05:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么?\N{\rEng}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:55.35,2:05:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是鱼子酱\N{\rEng}That's caviar.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:57.52,2:06:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那些呢?  -无花果\N{\rEng}- What are those? - These are figs.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:00.85,2:06:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个呢?\N{\rEng}And that?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:05.10,2:06:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个吗?\N{\rEng}This?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:08.10,2:06:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想你不会喜欢\N{\rEng}That I don't think you would like.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:10.52,2:06:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-看起来很好吃  -是很好吃\N{\rEng}- It looks good. - Oh, it is good.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:12.89,2:06:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能尝尝吗?\N{\rEng}Can I have some?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:15.72,2:06:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是个很奇怪的孩子\N{\rEng}You're a very unusual boy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:18.52,2:06:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不喜欢吃他们给我的食物\N{\rEng}I couldn't eat what they gave me.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:19.97,2:06:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,依我看来那根本不是食物\N{\rEng}Nor should you. It isn't even food...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:22.06,2:06:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我才自己带吃的来\N{\rEng}as I understand the definition, which is why I always bring my own.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:28.23,2:06:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么你想吃哪一种?\N{\rEng}So, which would you like to try?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:35.10,2:06:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想应该没关系吧\N{\rEng}Well, I suppose it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:39.19,2:06:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟  你我的妈妈都曾说过这句话\N{\rEng}After all, as your mother tells you, and my mother certainly told me...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.14,2:06:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记得她常说 "重要的是..."\N{\rEng}"It is important," she always used to say...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:46.73,2:06:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"要不断尝试不同的东西"\N{\rEng}"always to try new things."
Dialogue: 0,2:06:49.69,2:06:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘴张开\N{\rEng}Open up.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:06.65,2:11:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回见  "汉"\N{\rEng}Ta-ta. "H."


